text:
the times when world is talking about women’s assault, 
it negates that the identity of abuser and abused is gender-neutral

for -
every-time my cousin forced herself upon me,
whenever my teacher touched my penis,
my uncle pushed me to give him a blowjob,
my senior made me watch porn,
that shopkeeper grabbed me and forced me to give him a hand-job,
whenever the watchman had raped me,

i lay frozen,
paralysed for life,
speechless for eternity,
pondering over my situation,
will anyone believe me?

the world where boys will always be boys,
forgets that victims have no gender,
perpetrators have no ethics and gender,

who will believe the atrocities of a guy?
when he is not even allowed to cry,
where he is a symbol of power,
but left to be weak in shower

what are we - victims of time? or victims of gender? or victims of perceived notions?
why are guys told to be strong day in and day out,
when the world is waiting to rip them apart,
where is my safe heaven?
where are my protectors?
i know i need to be my own

yet, here i stand shattered,
battered for life,
with no place to call mine,
having no relations to trust upon,
with constant feelings of shame,
of disgust,
of helplessness.
still i give myself courage to move on, 
for this day shall also pass.
.
.
.
- anonymous

text: real time post. it is 2:30 am on a thursday night. i am home from an awesome night of dancing with friends. i am sober but happy and oblivious because i had such a wonderful time with my friends. i am nearly 40 years old. i am what many people concider "fat". i am no where near what is concidered a "babe" or a classic beauty. the only skin i am showing is my face, and only because it is october and i am cold. i am in my own "safe" neighbourhood. a man just double backed in his car to try and pick me up at the bus stop. another man, someone who would appear to be sketchy because he is transient, made a point of taking the bus with me because he saw "a creepy guy stop and stare at you" and he wanted to make sure i got off the bus safe. i did get off the bus safe, but the man in the car followed me into the mcdonald's, and approached me again. i had to tell him (very reluctantly) that my husband was waiting for me at home. the half block [speed] walk home was one of the scariest in my life. i am shaking with fear. i am thankful that i live in a home with two powerful roommates and a lot of big dogs. to all of those people who think that the me too movement is going too far. to all of those that think a woman must be asking for it, must look a certain way, must be dressed or looking seductive, must be asking for it-  fuck you!!!! this is every woman's experience. this is happening everyday. this is not right. fucking #metoo

text:
從她的音樂作品中，我知道她有創作能力、歌聲動人；
從super ball和oscar典禮的表演裡，我知道她有驚人的舞台魅力；
從種種時尚盛會中，我看到她特別的穿搭風格；
從電影「一個巨星的誕生a star is born」，我看到她的清新演技和踏入新領域的勇氣；
elle雜誌舉辦了25th “women in hollywood event”，她發表的演說充滿了力量，沒有藉機宣傳自己初登場的電影，而是為女性發聲，揭露了自己滿是傷痕的過去，鼓勵女性站起來、看重自己。台上的她，沒有生牛肉裝，沒有華服，沒有招牌恨天高，沒有艷妝或假髮，只有oversized的褲裝，和真實又勇敢的—lady gaga。
佩服妳，也向妳致敬。
————————————————

text:
dussehra is a major hindu festival observed for different reasons and celebrated differently in various parts of the indian subcontinent, significantly quoting a natural example of victory of good (dharma) over evil (adharma). we burn effigies of ravana as a symbol of victory of good over bad.

however, if we look inwards, pride, anger, ego and social evils like gender inequality still persist across the world. this dussehra lets strive to be kind to each other and towards removing these social evils from our society.

you stopped me from speaking the truth, you used me to fulfill your desires, you abused my body to satisfy your lust, you dumped me when i lost my youth, your physical strength pinned me down every time i raised my voice. but i won't stop, i shall rise from the ashes and confront you,  you can no longer overpower me, you can no longer treat me like your slave, you can't shame me, blame me, condemn me just because i am a woman.

text:
#metoo och vårt feministiska självförsvar

vi kvinnor har länge varit bra på att dela erfarenheter, vi har samlats i rum och forum på olika sätt i olika tider för att dela vår vardag med varandra. egentligen inte för att det varit ett stort nöje, även om jag själv njuter av rum med bara tjejer, utan för att det varit nödvändigt. vi har behövt mötas för att forma strategier mot det sexualiserade våld vi alla kollektivt upplever. #metoo var ett tydligt exempel på det behovet, kämpar vi ensamma är vi inte starkare än en liten vindpust, men kämpar vi tillsammans kan vi bli en orkan. vi i ung vänster har i snart 20 år arbetat med och utvecklat praktiken feministiskt självförsvar. en enligt mig fantastisk praktik som sammanfattar det starkaste och viktigaste för en feministisk rörelse – skuldbefriande och systerskap.

i självförsvaret möts vi tjejer och kvinnor i separatistiska rum och använder hela oss, såväl sinnen som kropp, för att bilda en motkraft mot sexualiserat våld. tillsammans konstaterar vi att det är ett gemensamt problem vi alla möter, oavsett om det är en obehaglig blick på busshållplatsen, killar som tafsar i skolkorridoren eller en kontrollerande och våldsam partner. vi bär erfarenheterna tillsammans. våra kroppar ses ofta som passiva, som objekt gjorda för någon annans skull och inte för vår egen. det vill vi ändra på och därför har vi tagit det i egna händer. feministiskt självförsvar är fysiskt, psykiskt och verbalt. vi använder vår styrka när vi slår och vi testar gränser för våra röster. 
idag är vi i ung vänster stolta över att få förvalta vårt självförsvar, vi håller kontinuerligt pass på allt från högstadieskolor till arbetsplatser och kvinnojourer. vi har exporterat praktiken till bland annat norge, palestina och colombia, och varje år utbildar vi nya instruktörer för att kunna vara på fler platser och hålla fler pass. vetskapen av att tusentals kvinnor i sverige och internationellt någon gång varit på ett pass i feministiskt självförsvar och tillsammans ropar ”nej!”, den ger hopp och kraft till att fortsätta kämpa.

dina viksten abrahamson, ordförande för ung vänsters feministiska utskott

text:
munculnya kampanye gerakan #metoo di industri film bollywood yang diawali oleh aktris tanushree dutta (yang melaporkan aktor nana patekar ke jalur hukum atas kasus pelecehan seks), kini terus bermunculan para artis yang melaporkan para seleb yang terlibat kasus pelecehan seks maupun perkosaan

dan untuk kali ini, giliran penyanyi playback shweta pandit yang melaporkan penata musik handal anu malik. namun sebelum shweta melaporkan, sebenarnya penyanyi cantik sona mohapatra juga telah lebih dulu  telah menuduh anu malik sebagai pelaku seks berantai

dalam cuitan di akun twitternya, shweta pandit menulis, "harus kembali ke ingatan terburuk saya sebagai seorang gadis remaja hari ini untuk menulis ini dan berbicara, sekarang atau tidak sama sekali. ini adalah #metoo saya dan harus memperingatkan gadis-gadis muda lainnya tentang #anumalik & memberi tahu anda #timesup @indiametoo. terima kasih @sonamohapatra karena telah berbicara tentang dia & mendukung ini

shweta teringat saat diminta oleh anu malik untuk menciumnya, ketika dia masih berusia 15 tahun di empire studio saat sedang rekaman, dalam sebuah album soundtrack film bersama penyanyi playback lainnya yaitu shaan dan sunidhi chauhan.

shweta mengatakan bahwa anu malik telah akrab dan mengenal seluruh keluarganya. bahkan anu malik telah menganggap ayah shweta sebagai seorang bhai (kakak). lebih jauh lagi, anu bahkan memiliki anak perempuan yang  seusia dengan dirinya, tetapi itu tidak menghentikannya untuk mengeksploitasi wanita lain, baik gadis kecil ataupun remaja. shweta pun menyebut penata musik top itu sebagai seorang pedofil.

lain halnya dengan shweta, sona mohapatra juga bercerita tentang insiden dengan anu malik. dimana saat itu, anu malik memanggilnya dengan panggilan 'maal', dengan nada cabul dan melecehkannya secara seksual

shweta pandit  berterima kasih kepada sona mahapatra  karena telah berani berbicara dan mengekspos tentang kelakuan anu malik yang tidak senonoh

sementara itu, sang komposer anu malik menolak bertemu sona mohapatra, bahkan anu menyebut tuduhan shweta tersebut konyol
.
"no comment! ini benar-benar konyol. saya tidak ingin membicarakannya. saat ini setiap orang bisa berkata apapun

dalam cuitan di akun twitternya, shweta pandit menulis, "harus kembali ke ingatan terburuk saya sebagai seorang gadis remaja hari ini untuk menulis ini dan berbicara, sekarang atau tidak sama sekali. ini adalah  saya dan harus memperingatkan gadis-gadis muda lainnya tentang  & memberi tahu anda   terima kasih  karena telah berbicara tentang dia & mendukung ini

shweta teringat saat diminta oleh anu malik untuk menciumnya, ketika dia masih berusia 15 tahun di empire studio saat sedang rekaman, dalam sebuah album soundtrack film bersama penyanyi playback lainnya yaitu shaan dan sunidhi chauhan.

shweta mengatakan bahwa anu malik telah akrab dan mengenal seluruh keluarganya. bahkan anu malik telah menganggap ayah shweta sebagai seorang bhai (kakak). lebih jauh lagi, anu bahkan memiliki anak perempuan yang  seusia dengan dirinya, tetapi itu tidak menghentikannya untuk mengeksploitasi wanita lain, baik gadis kecil ataupun remaja. shweta pun menyebut penata musik top itu sebagai seorang pedofil.

lain halnya dengan shweta, sona mohapatra juga bercerita tentang insiden dengan anu malik. dimana saat itu, anu malik memanggilnya dengan panggilan 'maal', dengan nada cabul dan melecehkannya secara seksual

shweta pandit  beerima kasih kepada sona mahapatra  karena telah berani berbicara dan mengekspos tentang kelakuan anu malik yang tidak senonoh

sementara itu, sang komposer anu malik menolak beemu sona mohapatra, bahkan anu menyebut tuduhan shweta tersebut konyol

text:
tell your stories. tell your truth. keep talking. get mad. keep supporting other abuse survivors. a year after the birth of the #metoo movement, much has changed and nothing has changed. victim blaming is on the rise again having seen and experienced it myself from fans, friends, and other people @adamcroasdell has enlisted towards myself and his other victims shows me how malicious and unsafe this world can be for victims. using young impressionable fans to shame and silence his victims shows how far we have to go to make victims feel safe from these abusers. actions from them and him is #whyididntreport on top of living in fear of him and their threats. my silence gave him a thirst for more and younger victims. i realize and know wholeheartedly he will never stop. his fans, friends, and family are his accomplices by victim shaming and he shows no remorse for the pain he causes he feels proud. in other words, if you’re waiting for them to make an apology, forget it. these men might regret getting caught. but expressing true remorse about the damage they caused isn’t forthcoming. what most of them haven’t lost is the conviction that since they are either celebrities, men in power from business to political power they have the right to treat women as they please, not the women we are to bow down live with the nightmare. i decided to no longer suffer in silence but men like adam croasdell we stand up to or say no to feel they are the real victims and, as such, do not need to change their behavior and continue the cycle of abuse making it worse and enlist others to abuse their victims. adam croasdell is one of the many men during the #metoo era included in some of the most shameful chapters in the history of the united states because it shows his complicity and what men of his caliber will do to hurt women and hide it.

name: Break The Silence
tweet_full:
tell your stories. tell your truth. keep talking. get mad. keep supporting other abuse survivors. a year after the birth of the #metoo movement, much has changed and nothing has changed. victim blaming is on the rise again having seen and experienced it myself from fans, friends, and other people @adamcroasdell has enlisted towards myself and his other victims shows me how malicious and unsafe this world can be for victims. using young impressionable fans to shame and silence his victims shows how far we have to go to make victims feel safe from these abusers. actions from them and him is #whyididntreport on top of living in fear of him and their threats. my silence gave him a thirst for more and younger victims. i realize and know wholeheartedly he will never stop. his fans, friends, and family are his accomplices by victim shaming and he shows no remorse for the pain he causes he feels proud. in other words, if you’re waiting for them to make an apology, forget it. these men might regret getting caught. but expressing true remorse about the damage they caused isn’t forthcoming. what most of them haven’t lost is the conviction that since they are either celebrities, men in power from business to political power they have the right to treat women as they please, not the women we are to bow down live with the nightmare. i decided to no longer suffer in silence but men like adam croasdell we stand up to or say no to feel they are the real victims and, as such, do not need to change their behavior and continue the cycle of abuse making it worse and enlist others to abuse their victims. adam croasdell is one of the many men during the #metoo era included in some of the most shameful chapters in the history of the united states because it shows his complicity and what men of his caliber will do to hurt women and hide it.

text: via @buzzfeednews || the retired lakers star was removed from the jury of the animation is film festival after a 2003 rape allegation against him resurfaced online. the move reportedly came after a petition was posted last week on change.org urging the festival organisers to remove bryant. bryant responded to the festival’s decision in a statement saying he was “disappointed,” but motivated to build a studio "that focuses on diversity and inclusion in storytelling." in 2003, bryant was accused of sexually assaulting a colorado hotel employee. the charges were dropped once his accuser refused to testify, and bryant made a public apology and settled with the woman in a civil lawsuit in 2005. (📸: getty)

text:
#metoo och vårt feministiska självförsvar

vi kvinnor har länge varit bra på att dela erfarenheter, vi har samlats i rum och forum på olika sätt i olika tider för att dela vår vardag med varandra. egentligen inte för att det varit ett stort nöje, även om jag själv njuter av rum med bara tjejer, utan för att det varit nödvändigt. vi har behövt mötas för att forma strategier mot det sexualiserade våld vi alla kollektivt upplever. #metoo var ett tydligt exempel på det behovet, kämpar vi ensamma är vi inte starkare än en liten vindpust, men kämpar vi tillsammans kan vi bli en orkan. vi i ung vänster har i snart 20 år arbetat med och utvecklat praktiken feministiskt självförsvar. en enligt mig fantastisk praktik som sammanfattar det starkaste och viktigaste för en feministisk rörelse – skuldbefriande och systerskap.

i självförsvaret möts vi tjejer och kvinnor i separatistiska rum och använder hela oss, såväl sinnen som kropp, för att bilda en motkraft mot sexualiserat våld. tillsammans konstaterar vi att det är ett gemensamt problem vi alla möter, oavsett om det är en obehaglig blick på busshållplatsen, killar som tafsar i skolkorridoren eller en kontrollerande och våldsam partner. vi bär erfarenheterna tillsammans. våra kroppar ses ofta som passiva, som objekt gjorda för någon annans skull och inte för vår egen. det vill vi ändra på och därför har vi tagit det i egna händer. feministiskt självförsvar är fysiskt, psykiskt och verbalt. vi använder vår styrka när vi slår och vi testar gränser för våra röster. 
idag är vi i ung vänster stolta över att få förvalta vårt självförsvar, vi håller kontinuerligt pass på allt från högstadieskolor till arbetsplatser och kvinnojourer. vi har exporterat praktiken till bland annat norge, palestina och colombia, och varje år utbildar vi nya instruktörer för att kunna vara på fler platser och hålla fler pass. vetskapen av att tusentals kvinnor i sverige och internationellt någon gång varit på ett pass i feministiskt självförsvar och tillsammans ropar ”nej!”, den ger hopp och kraft till att fortsätta kämpa.

dina viksten abrahamsson, ordförande för ung vänsters feministiska utskott

text:
if you weren’t there with us then you cannot judge. i will be speaking my truth everyday until our joint interview airs. adam croasdell uses his friends and fans to shame his victims into silence five women are coming out what if there’s more out there we don’t yet know about? we have proof of his abuse. he choked me until almost unconsciousness it was not consensual i said stop 6 times and was gasping choking for air and then he proceeded to punch and kick me. should i or any other woman take his abuse because he’s an actor and you like his acting? we keep saying support victims let them speak their truth they are survivors and strong but adam croasdell is a strong example of misogyny and the abuse we as victims go through because they want to silence us. not one person who attacks his victims for shattering their illusions of who he is has taken the time to ask what happened or to see what we have to support the claims. adam croasdell has hurt multiple women and their families all to hide his wrongdoing and to present a false image for his career. no matter who adam enlists to silence or threaten us which some of us were threatened with bodily harm or try and guilt us his image or career does not mean more than a women’s life or safety. walk a mile in our well worn shoes ask us questions before you condemn what if it were you?  i’m proud to finally have the courage to not only admit that but speak out. i never want another woman to go through what we five have been put through by adam croasdell even if he uses fans or friends to attack us  and lies he can hide the truth from them but he can’t hide it long our interview airs next month.

text:
i noticed that a lot of people are depressed these days.
and i personally feel that it is as a result of lack of "enough" self love. they love themselves but not enough to take care of their health ,their heart and their soul.so much so that they are drowning in self pity and i am not excluding myself from the list. we are not perfect .but we can learn to love ourselves more than the depression that we feed daily.
so this is for all the people out there fighting depression. you will learn to love yourself and this time ....it will be more than enough.#fighting #depression
#youareloved #itwillbeok #metoo

text:
venus gets lots of good press and it’s not all warranted. “all is fair in love and war.” venus herself was a very jealous woman, she made her daughter-in-law’s life hell because she envied the youthful beauty and more importantly she envied that her son was focusing his attentions elsewhere. anyone who has dealt with a dickhead mother in law if familiar with this one! (💥on pondering this i have to point out that men have a venus too. it’s not so much a gender issue as a venus issue..) i’ve known plenty of bitchy men!
•
•

with venus retrograde in scorpio, we are not only calling out the men and sexual taboos - this is not just about the #metoo movement.  this is about calling out the duplicitous, shady, subtle, bitchy and manipulative bullshit that goes on in offices, families and friendship groups everywhere. 💥venus is “nice” she rules libra and is exalted in pisces… neither sign is known for it’s all out authenticity (where kindness is favoured over the truth, not necessarily a bad thing!). the thing with manipulation, game playing and all the games that go hand in hand with school child behaviour (that not all grow out of) is that eventually people catch on… them - whoever they might be, they eventually catch on.  i think that a venus retrograde in scorpio period is the perfect time to address both our inner bitch, the one that still wants to look the best, be the best and have the most attention and to call out those who are pulling strings and discreetly causing drama.  karma does it’s thing so don’t force the process, but it’s most certainly a good time to call a spade a spade.  there is healing found in the truth and with jupiter in scorpio and venus in her “light bearing” retrograde phase… the truth will out. p.s. men have a venus too! 💥
•

text:
broken,
my thoughts have been broken,

soaken,
my words have been soaken in the melancholy of life.

opened,
the wounds have been opened,

of the past which i thought have been healed.

broken,
my heart is about to get broken,

but this time i will give it a token to face the darkness with all its vigorous power.

every year , raavan is burned , though everyday sita is outraged.. she is strong.. she is fragile , she is brutal , she is strength.. so before the raavan in you is awake , tell urself you are even worse . cause if sita could defend herself by a stick , 21st century sita is  stronger than u can even imagine..
#dussehra #burntheraavanbeforeraavanburnsu

text:
नमस्ते folks! happy dussehra and congrats for more pollution. ☺ (sarcastic smile intended) also, navratri has come to an end, so how was it guys? tell me, since i don't celebrate much festivals (let's save the backstory for another time) for me, it wasn't really pleasing since on one side i got to read a new story under #metoo everyday and on the other side a bunch of people who don't even really know why navratri is celebrated danced on stupid sexist songs on full volume through the night in the name of a goddess! i bet there's more than 50 women who've been harassed and silenced in the pandal you last visited this navratri.
anyways, moving on...
it's good over evil always! ❤✨ no matter how cruel of a time this is, ache din aayenge, bas bharosa rakho! :))) and till then if you believe that you have the power to make any difference, then please take even the smallest step towards a better world! :d 💕
•

text:
vuélvela a tocar, como a las cuerdas de una guitarra. 
hazla vibrar, con el rugido de tus palabras.
querer verla brillar, cada noche entre las sabanas. 
aprende a bailar, por cada una de sus carcajadas.
hazla volar, para que entre tus brazos nunca se estrelle.
repite su nombre otra vez, para que tu voz siempre la llene.🖤✨💫🇮🇹
.
.
.
.

text:
📝l’édito de la semaine : « courtes lignes » par @erindoherty_elle 
la dernière fashion week parisienne a curieusement provo- qué l’ire de la presse outre-atlantique. l’objet ? le show @celine qui a marqué le retour très attendu de @hedislimane, bernard arnault lui ayant confié la direction artistique de la maison après le départ de phoebe philo. les américains n’ont pas du tout aimé : c’est leur droit. mais ce qui donne la chair de poule à une autre frange de journalistes mode, c’est le flot d’avis pour le moins réactionnaires sur ce que la mode pour les femmes doit être à l’ère post–#metoo. entre les lignes, des modèles jugés « trop courts »... jo ellison, du « financial times », a déploré « des robes de balle- rines déchirées dans lesquelles des jeunes filles de 17 ans pourraient faire le trottoir ». « the hollywood reporter » allant jusqu’à comparer hedi slimane à un « donald trump de la mode ».
le site vox a, lui, devisé : « les vêtements sont le reflet d’une époque. ils sont ce avec quoi nous nous armons pour avancer dans le monde. slimane a fait ce qu’il fait de mieux. mais le contexte a changé. il n’a pas su le voir. » depuis son départ de saint laurent en 2016 et après deux années off, monsieur slimane n’aurait-il donc pas avancé dans sa réflexion malgré un changement sociétal majeur ? que penser alors des journalistes mode érudits qui jugent pourtant, en 2018, qu’une jupe trop courte est incon- venante ? qui, de slimane ou des journalistes, exhume un débat centenaire et rance sur l’immodestie de la mode féminine ?
[1/2] par @erindoherty_elle, directrice de la rédaction 📸 abaca
#edito #magazineelle #ellefrance

text:
हम सिर्फ वही #metoo stories पढ़ रहे हैं जो social media पर share की गई हैं..कितनी ऐसी stories होंगी जो share नहीं की गई हैं..शर्म, झिझक, दर्द और डर से दिल दिमाग के किसी कोने में छुपी नासूर की तरह चुभ रही होंगी.. कितनी ऐसी औरतें हैं जो social media पर है ही नहीं..हर शहर  गाँव कसबे गली नुक्कड़ दफतर घर में करोड़ो #metoo stories होंगी जो कभी घर के बाहर कभी घर के अंदर घटी होंगी.. कभी ग़लत तरीके से देखा छुआ गया है, अभद्र अश्लील इशारे किए गए हैं, फ़बतियां कसी गई हैं, ताने मारे गए हैं ..तरह तरह से असहज महसूस कराया गया है, छेड़ा गया है..तेज़ाब फेंका गया है..rape किया गया है..विकृत मानसिकता का शिकार बनाया गया है!! कब आयेगा वो दसहरा जब इस मानसिकता रूपी रावण का हमेशा के लिए दहन हो जाएगा ?? कभी सोचा है.. ये राक्षसी मानसिकता आती कहाँ से है?? (ये video august 2017 में चंडीगढ़ में घटे शर्मनाक stalking incident के संदर्भ में बनाया गया था) full video link in bio.

text:
pssst... här finns stöd att få. 
ett år efter att #metoo fick ett stort genomslag har vissa förändringar skett. känslan av att inte vara ensam, möjligheterna att få prata ut och medvetenheten om sexualiserat våld har ökat. men det har inte slutat. vi arbetar utifrån att våld är så mycket mer än vad som brukar benämnas som våld. sexualiserat våld är också kommentarer, blickar, skämt, bilder som sprids, hot och uppmaningar. 
söker du efter någon att prata med om dina upplevelser? behöver du stöd och bearbetning? vi har sammanställt en stöd-lista till organisationer du kan vända dig till. den första listan riktar sig till barn och unga och den andra till vuxna. använda listan och sprid den gärna! 
ta hand om er och fortsätt kampen mot våldet! 
den här veckan lägger en kommun fri från våld extra fokus på #metoo och de möjligheterna som följt.
[syntolkning: den första bilden är en grön bild där det står ”pssst...”. den andra bilden är lista över telefonnummer för barn och unga. den tredje bilden är en lista över telefonnummer för vuxna]
name: En Kommun Fri Från Våld Borås

text:
the movement has really caught on in india & it’s beginning to show results. 
it’s about time !
for far too long, too many women & some men too have been victims of sexual harassment & exploitation by people in power. 
yes there are some grey areas.
yes there will be the oddball who is accused wrongly.
i do believe in the old adage - ‘innocent until proven guilty’
but my gut, my reasoning, understanding & experience tells me - almost all of the accusations will stand true.

more needs to be done. 
full support to anybody who has been a victim & brave enough to speak up

#metoo
#timesup
#webelieveyou

text:
@rosalienelson was told to lose even more weight after this image was taken by a uk agency in order to get ‘down to the bone’. rosalie started a petition that has over 191,599 signatures demanding the government step in to do something about dangerously thin models. 
thousands of people are scouted every day and then upon going to meet an agency, are told to lose weight or change something about themselves before they can be accepted, or simply rejected to their face. should these unregulated companies with no required qualifications for scouts, have the power to approach people on the street and subject them to their standard of beauty - bones and measurements?

text: morgen in unserer neuen ausgabe: jordan peterson, ein kanadischer psychologieprofessor und derzeit der wohl bekannteste kanadische intellektuelle, ist ein spaltpilz. millionen seiner fans stehen vermutlich millionen seiner gegner und gegnerinnen gegenüber. wer ihn liebt, und das sind vor allem männer, liebt ihn wie einen vater. peterson sagt, wie man sich verhalten soll in einer modernen welt mit sich verändernden werten und fliessenden geschlechterrollen. wer peterson nicht mag, hasst ihn in der regel. wirft ihm vor, politisch auf der rechten seite zu stehen, gar ein faschist zu sein. es gibt allerdings auch eine zwischenposition gegenüber peterson. dazu muss man ihn genau lesen, sich mit seinem werk, den vielen vorträgen, die digital zugänglich sind, vertieft auseinandersetzen. unser reporter mikael krogerus ist wochenlang ins peterson-universum eingetaucht. in dieser zeit haben wir über peterson viel geredet und gestritten. ausserdem: die chronik von brüssel. jahrelang hörte jeanne ponté von sexistischen übergriffen im eu-parlament. und schrieb alles auf. als das publik wird, ändert sich – fast nichts. und das ein jahr nach #metoo. wir wünschen ihnen eine spannende lektüre an einem entspannten wochenende! coverbild: aaron wynia @aaronwynia #tagimagi #dasmagazin #jordanpeterson #jeanneponté #euparlament #reportage #swissjournalism

text:
you are literally hunted. disturbing, but true. so how do you know you’re being studied by a sociopath when their tests are innocuous and they’re all happening while you’re distracted by intentionally staged lovebombing?
.
well, for starters, know this.
.
it isn’t healthy to have your boundaries questioned or crossed in the beginning of a relationship.
.
it isn’t healthy for a relationship to move beyond your comfort zone in order to satisfy someone else’s timeline.
.
it isn’t healthy to fight in the beginning of a relationship and then be begged for forgiveness or hit with pity ploys.
.
hollow, apathetic, empty, rehearsed, lackluster, or blame shifting apologies aren’t healthy. if you listen in, you can hear these in someone’s tone of voice.
.
having your feelings and concerns minimized isn’t healthy.
.
being pulled away from your friends and enmeshed into someone else’s world isn’t healthy.
.
asking about/sharing information about personal finances early on isn’t healthy.
.
being swept off your feet with opulence isn’t healthy. 🥂🎩👑 it’s okay to like the finer things, but over-indulgence is a major red flag. it can be a distraction or a manipulation tactic. and it can speak volumes of someone’s values, priorities, and self worth. 💛🦋

सुना है - कुछ पत्थर उछले हैं,
पूरी ताक़त से, नसों की भींचकर,
रग़ों को आसमाँ तक खींचकर,
अच्छा है कि अब नसें इस्पात सी हैं,
रग़ों में ख़ून था, अब आग सी है,
इन्ही के दम से ये पत्थर है उछला,
सलाम, हिम्मत से उछले पत्थरों को,
औ एहतिराम ऐसी हिम्मत का.
सुनो ऐ पत्थरों!
तुम ख़ूब उछलो, और तोड़ दो,
हर पथरीले आवरण, आडम्बर,
और भर दो मालिक मकाँ के अंदर,
अपनी हिम्मत का डर. ~दिलीप पाण्डेय *इस बार विजयादशमी से पहले ही कई रावण दिखे, डरे, मरे... जो राम बनते थे. इस बार शक्तिस्वरूपा माँ दुर्गा ने कईयों रूप धरे, असुरों का संहार किया. इस बार पर्व ने अपने भाव और मर्म को जिया. तो इस बार सभी को समानता, सच्चाई, हिम्मत और न्याय वाली दशहरा की निस्सीम मंगलकामनाएं. जय हो!* ~दिलीप पाण्डेय

text:
does this scenario sound familiar? actually, it’s too familiar and too dangerous to ignore. you might forget what they said, 👉🏽 but you will never forget how they made you feel. 
don't normalize abuse. don’t enable it by being complicit. what you ignore, you empower. what you allow will continue unless you stop enabling it. pay attention to signs 🚦. 👉🏽 no reason gives anyone the right to be cruel or rude to you. if they find a "reason" once, they'll find a reason to hurt you again & again. a genuine apology shouldn't have a "but" attached to it. it's either they’re sorry or they’re not! rectify; don't justify. don’t be a doormat. assert yourself. you deserve better.
———————————————————— ‎عندما يزعجك تصرف ما من أهل بيتك ، إتقِ الله فيهم. لك الحق أن "تغضب" و لكن ليس لك الحق أن "تغلط" لا بيدك و لا بلسانك ⛔️ الإعتذار لا يكفي و خصوصاً إذا صَحِبَهُ أسباب أو تبرير. على سبيل المثال: أنا غلطان "لكن"  كنت تعبان، كنت مشغول، كنت خايف إخسرك ، كنت خايف تتركيني ، كنت في إجتماع ، كنت جوعان ، كنت عالتليفون ، إلخ ... كلمة "لكن" ليست مبرراً و لا يقبلها حتى القاضي لأن ليس هناك أي سبب يُبَرر "الجريمة". نعم ، التهديد و الوعيد "جريمة" و السب و التعدي بالضرب "جريمة"  يُعاقب عليها القانون 👨🏻‍✈️ هذا هو الحال لو غلطت على الغريب فكيف هو الحال مع القريب ؟ لا تستخف في حق القريب. القريب أولى من الغريب. التسامح لمن "يعترف" لا لمن يبرر أو يتنصل من المسؤولية و "يتمسكن حتى يتمكن" لحفظ ماء الوجه إلى أن يأتي فعلته مرة ثانية و ثالثة... الطبع يغلب التطبع. "تسامحوا بس لا تصيروا ممسحة." الدنيا مليانة مماسح لا تصيروا إحصائية. رَحِمَ الله إِمرءٍ عَرَفَ قَدرَ نَفسه فوقف عِنده.  و الله من وراء القصد

text:
varför kallar vi oss medusa?
namnet kommer från den grekiska mytologin och syftar till medusa som blev våldtagen av poseidon i athenas tempel. som straff för att ha besudlat templet och förnärmat athena fick hon ormar som hår och ett ansikte som förvandlade alla som tittade på henne till sten. det var alltså inte poseidon, utan medusa som straffades och blev till ett monster. det här är en historia som vi vet att många överlevare känner igen sig i.

text:
#서울여성회 #페미니스트 #페미니즘 #여성주의 #서울여성문화축제 #여성영화 #미투 #metoo #withyou #아니타힐 #영화상영제 #korea_feminist #feminist #서울시청 #11월17일 
12회 서울여성문화축제 ‘너희가 바라는 피해자는 없다’

매년 진행되고 있는 서울여성문화축제가 올해엔 장소를 실내로 옮겨 영화 [아니타힐]상영 및 전시, gv를 진행하고자 합니다. 미투운동은 피해자가 다른 사람들에게 용기를 주고, 투쟁을 불러일으키고, 세상을 바꾸는 주체라는 것을 세상에 드러냈습니다. 그러나 피해자를 바라보는 우리사회의 시선은 미투운동을 가로막는 방해물이자 미투운동이 바꾸어야할 문제 그 자체입니다. 사회가 요구하는 피해자다움이 미투운동을 부정하고 피해자의 용기있는 목소리를 막으려 할 때 우리는 외쳐야 합니다. 
너희가 바라는 그런 피해자는 없다! 
피해는 존재가 아니라 경험일 뿐이며, 피해자는 동정의 대상이 아니라 투쟁의 주체이다! 
일시: 2018년 11월 17일(토) 14:00~18:00 
장소: 서울시청 후생동강당 
프로그램 : 영화 [아니타힐] 상영 및 gv 
자세한 내용 확인하기 : https://bit.ly/2s0fpmi 
신청하러가기 : bit.ly/너희가바라는피해자는없다

text:
when you allow the divine masculine to hold you. 
this is what it looks like. ✨
.
.
.
as i geared up to share my most vulnerable share yet.. after a sea of calm, i felt a panic arise
the wounds 
began to yell at me and say
what 
no
you can’t go there
it’s not safe
don’t talk about it
who cares anyway
stay here

i took that little girl in my arms and let her know
it’s okay
as i sat and heard words of poetry spun out of my truth-telling
in the moment i decided to stop being so strong 
and just let myself crack a little
somehow this shining light showed up
a soul in communion from afar
in the himalayas
and guided me through the tender moments

his presence
and fierce gentleness
proved to me
as other beautiful men have also
that it’s actually safe
it’s safe
to share
now
it’s safe to be
it’s safe to speak my truth.

i remembered
what it felt like
to fully soften
to trust again
to let my guard down
while keeping my eyes open
heart open

it’s safe.

ancestral pain.. witch burnings, and the events of this lifetime 
made me believe otherwise

i felt like showing up was ‘too much’
as if speaking my truth was asking for too much attention.
receding so as not to shine for too long.
not allowing myself to just express 
fully
consistently 
what was brimming over from my soul.

this is what it looks like to be held by the masculine divine.

miracles happen.
pain thaws.
breath relaxes and deepens.
trauma, dislodges
space is created.
for healing, sacred.

full feeling, invited.
depths of grief, invited.
suppression, shown the door.
we don’t need you anymore
thank you for your service.
i know i needed you to learn all this.
you can go now.. what follows shortly is

closure
clarity
catharsis 
self-expression
freedom
release

this is what it looks like to be held by the divine masculine.

pure presence
unconditional love 
devotion for the divine feminine in 
all her glory, all her forms

no expectations
no end game
no games, period.
no manipulation
no false bravado and macho bs

it’s the true way of being.
what we are all here to return to.
vulnerability
communication
communion
unity
and no holds barred open adoration.
#newnormal 👇🏽

text:
i was young and the world was mine
i could get anything anytime
step into my room and i'd sing your song
and your clothes would come off before long

but i was a boy and you were a girl 
and you were my toy.. but i was your world
didn't even notice when you'd stay up and cry all night
i was too caught up in myself to make it right
guess a boy like me couldn't understand
what you needed
you needed a man

she was wild like a night in spain
we made love before i knew her name 
god it felt so good just to lose control 
couldn't see i was losing my soul

thought i was your boy and you were my girl 
but i was a toy caught up in your world
didn't see it comin' when you threw my heart to the floor
i was so caught up in you i came back for more 
but a girl like you helped me understand
what i needed to grow into a man

it took a cold-hearted lover to change my ways
to see that love without respect is not okay
now a boy like me has come to understand
what it means
to really be a man — makana #lyrics #poet #poetsofig #songwriting #song #music #songlyrics #man #lover #boy #girl #inlove #love #relationship #realtalk #metoo #healing #realman #menstyle #guitarist #hawaii photo: lexi mackenzie

text:
a call for justice against the harassment...! .
the year 2018 has been a blessing for all women which is a testimony to strengthen their existence in our country. the initiative was taken with the very step of ‘beti bachao, beti padhao’ and the another one is taken recently by allowing the women of all age groups (10 to 50 years) in the sacred ‘sabarimala’ temple of kerala. everything could be related to the women empowerment. a woman is no longer inferior to her male counterpart. she is the light of lamp that lightens the world around with her divine light. so, it is the responsibility of every individual to respect her in all possible ways.

the #metoo movement that has gone worldwide is the best platform for all women to gather and rise a voice against the harassment they have faced in their earlier years at workplace. every woman that came forward through social media is an example for another to fight back. they have been harbouring a volcano of those harassments that happened with them, has now erupted out with the capacity to burn the culprits. this movement has provided the road to their battle and the only ultimate goal is to make sure that every culprit gets a punishment for their did. many of us blamed the women that why did they take this much of years to come forward and narrate what happened to them. but, the fact is that many culprits belong to the high society having the status of invulnerable, so this suppressed her voice and the courage to fight the battle.

but, as it is said that the truth can never be suppressed and the light of truth will shine one day. this helped women to muster courage and come forward for the justice that they owe from their culprits. #metoo india needs to provide all the support to them so that every man from now onwards will think thousand times before touching his colleague with a bad intention of harassing her. and another thing to be changed is the hypocritical attitude of judging a woman by the type of clothes she wears. (continued below in comment section..:-)
name: Pradnya Gautam
tweet_full:
a call for justice against the harassment...! .
the year 2018 has been a blessing for all women which is a testimony to strengthen their existence in our country. the initiative was taken with the very step of ‘beti bachao, beti padhao’ and the another one is taken recently by allowing the women of all age groups (10 to 50 years) in the sacred ‘sabarimala’ temple of kerala. everything could be related to the women empowerment. a woman is no longer inferior to her male counterpart. she is the light of lamp that lightens the world around with her divine light. so, it is the responsibility of every individual to respect her in all possible ways.

the #metoo movement that has gone worldwide is the best platform for all women to gather and rise a voice against the harassment they have faced in their earlier years at workplace. every woman that came forward through social media is an example for another to fight back. they have been harbouring a volcano of those harassments that happened with them, has now erupted out with the capacity to burn the culprits. this movement has provided the road to their battle and the only ultimate goal is to make sure that every culprit gets a punishment for their did. many of us blamed the women that why did they take this much of years to come forward and narrate what happened to them. but, the fact is that many culprits belong to the high society having the status of invulnerable, so this suppressed her voice and the courage to fight the battle.

but, as it is said that the truth can never be suppressed and the light of truth will shine one day. this helped women to muster courage and come forward for the justice that they owe from their culprits. #metoo india needs to provide all the support to them so that every man from now onwards will think thousand times before touching his colleague with a bad intention of harassing her. and another thing to be changed is the hypocritical attitude of judging a woman by the type of clothes she wears. (continued below in comment section..:-)

text:
«я знаю, на что способны мужчины»: истории девушек, которые столкнулись с сексуальным насилием

фото @vadimbraydov ⠀
четыре смелые девушки решились рассказать горобзор.ру о своем горьком опыте, когда им пришлось столкнуться с сексуальным насилием. они предпочли не раскрывать своих имен и лиц по личным причинам. девушки считают, что об этом нужно и важно говорить. они больше не хотят бояться мужчин. 
что такое сексуальное насилие? 
сексуальное насилие, по определению всемирной организации здравоохранения, – это любой сексуальный акт или попытка его совершить. в это понятие также входят нежелательные сексуальные замечания или заигрывания. любые действия против сексуальности человека с использованием принуждения, совершаемые любым человеком независимо от его взаимоотношений с жертвой, в любом месте, включая дом и работу, так же относятся к насилию. уголовный кодекс россии предусматривает статью за «сексуальное насилие» (ст. 132 ук рф). российское законодательство под «изнасилованием» рассматривает только физический контакт, то есть вагинальный половой акт мужчины с женщиной, совершенное с применением физической силы или под угрозой ее применения. по данным мвд рб за 6 месяцев 2018 года, в башкирии количество изнасилований на 100 тысяч человек составило 55. в реальности изнасилование, его попытки и сексуальное насилие происходят намного чаще. по статистике, в полицию обращаются только от 8 до 14% женщин, переживших сексуальное насилие. если обратиться к историям, которые публикуют женщины в сети с хэштегами #янебоюсьсказать и #metoo, то можно увидеть, сколько случаев насилия остались скрыты по тем или иным причинам.
⠀

⠀

text:
#metoo

ये कहना और सोचना बहुत आसान है कि कैसे चुप थी वो अब तक? 
पर ये सोचना और समझना कठिन है कि क्योँ चुप रही वो अब तक?
वो चुप है क्योँ कि कानून नहीं है सख्त,
वो चुप है क्योँ कि समाज है बेशरम,
वो चुप है क्योँ कि लोग उसको कहेंगे बद्चलन,
वो चुप है क्योँ कि उसकी गलतियों का अम्बार लगाया जायेगा पहले,
वो चुप है क्योँ कि शब्दों से भी उसे नंगा किया जायेगा फिर…

मर्द है इसलिए उसको छू लिया, मर्द है इसलिए उसको छेड़ दिया,
मर्द है इसलिए उसका का रेप करदिया, मर्द है इसलिए अपनी ताकत से डरा दिया तूने,
औरत की कोख से जनके भी ये मर्दानगी दिखाई है तूने... मर्द है तो समझ पहले कि,
वो पलटे तो प्यार नही सम्मान है तेरा, वो तेरे बुलाने पे घर आये तो मौका नहीं विश्वास है तुझपे,
वो दो घूंट जाम के लगाले तेरे साथ तो आवारा नहीं दोस्त है तेरी… क्योँ देवी के आगे सर झुकाता है,
क्योँ नवरात्री में उपवास रखता है,
कितना पापी है तेरा मन जो पत्थर को तो देवी पूजता है,
और देवी के स्त्री रूप में बस हवस ढूंढता है… और शर्मिंदा मत कर स्त्री की गरिमा को क्योँ कि,
ऐसा न हो कि एक दिन तेरे घर से भी निकल आये एक आवाज़  #metoo…

लेखराज...
www.lekhrajworld.com

इस बार ये कविता नहीं कटाक्ष  है, मर्दों को समझना जरुरी है कि घर के बाहर की औरत और उनके घर की औरत सब से पहले एक महिला है उनकी गन्दी और हवस भरी प्यास बुझाने का साधन नहीं... share so may be in future we will not have such #metoo movement... you can follow lekhraj on insta & youtube@

text:
хотите,чтобы ребенок поскорее уснул?☺️
после 4 месяцев сон ребенка меняется. теперь начинают действовать ассоциации на засыпание. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ 💤ассоциации на засыпание – это условия, которые помогают человеку уснуть. привычная подушка, способ укутаться одеялом перед сном, любимая поза.☕️🍫 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
игрушка, «спящая» рядом с ребенком, тоже является ассоциацией на засыпание. 
она находится рядом с малышом при засыпании, остается в кроватке на всю ночь. 🙂⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ при пробуждении ребенок обнаружит ее рядом с собой и сможет спокойно продолжить сон 💤– «все в порядке, все так же, как было во время укладывания, ничего не изменилось».🤗💤💤💤 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ в первые месяцы жизни малыша такие игрушки-компаньоны ему не так уж и нужны, а вот начиная с 6 ☝🏻месяцев использовать их очень даже рекомендуется. ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀
что нужно иметь в виду, выбирая игрушку для сна? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⭐️удобство
вашей крохе должно быть комфортно обнимать и держать игрушку рядом с собой, а потому, размер выбирайте не слишком большой и не совсем маленький ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
⭐️безопасность
у игрушки, которая предназначена для сна не должно быть острых частей и деталей, которые могут поцарапать или навредить малышу. 
глазки, носики и прочие пластиковые детали должны быть очень хорошо закреплены, ведь малыш может захотеть их погрызть. лучше не рисковать и предложить ребенку игрушку без таких элементов, например, с вышитой мордочкой. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⭐️экологичность
вы должны быть уверены в том, что материалы, из которых сделана игрушка, безопасны, а их наполнитель и красители безвредны. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⭐️цвета
обходите стороной яркие расцветки. игрушка, которая предназначена для засыпания должна успокаивать, а не вызывать бурю эмоций. пастельные, приглушенные кофетные тона – то, что нужно!

после 4 месяцев сон ребенка меняется. теперь начинают действовать ассоциации на засыпание. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ 💤ассоциации на засыпание – это условия, которые помогают человеку уснуть. привычная подушка, способ укутаться одеялом перед сном, любимая поза.☕️🍫 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀
игрушка, «спящая» рядом с ребенком, тоже является ассоциацией на засыпание. 
она находится рядом с малышом при засыпании, остается в кроватке на всю ночь. 🙂⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ при пробуждении ребенок обнаружит ее рядом с собой и сможет спокойно продолжить сон 💤– «все в порядке, все так же, как было во время укладывания, ничего не изменилось».🤗💤💤💤 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ в первые месяцы жизни малыша такие игрушки-компаньоны ему не так уж и нужны, а вот начиная с 6 ☝🏻месяцев использовать их очень даже рекомендуется. ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀
что нужно иметь в виду, выбирая игрушку для сна? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⭐️удобство
вашей крохе должно быть комфортно обнимать и держать игрушку рядом с собой, а потому, размер выбирайте не слишком большой и не совсем маленький ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
⭐️безопасность
у игрушки, которая предназначена для сна не должно быть острых частей и деталей, которые могут поцарапать или навредить малышу. 
глазки, носики и прочие пластиковые детали должны быть очень хорошо закреплены, ведь малыш может захотеть их погрызть. лучше не рисковать и предложить ребенку игрушку без таких элементов, например, с вышитой мордочкой. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⭐️экологичность
вы должны быть уверены в том, что материалы, из которых сделана игрушка, безопасны, а их наполнитель и красители безвредны. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⭐️цвета
обходите стороной яркие расцветки. игрушка, которая предназначена для засыпания должна успокаивать, а не вызывать бурю эмоций. пастельные, приглушенные кофетные тона – то, что нужно!
⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀
а какие у вас или вашего ребенка ассоциации на засыпание? ♥️♥️♥️♥️♥️♥️⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀

stop_filter_tweet: хотите , чтобы ребенок поскорее уснул ? ☺️ после 4 месяцев сон ребенка меняется . теперь начинают действовать ассоциации на засыпание . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ 💤ассоциации на засыпание – это условия , которые помогают человеку уснуть . привычная подушка , способ укутаться одеялом перед сном , любимая поза.☕️🍫 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀ игрушка , « спящая » рядом с ребенком , тоже является ассоциацией на засыпание . она находится рядом с малышом при засыпании , остается в кроватке на всю ночь . 🙂⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ при пробуждении ребенок обнаружит ее рядом с собой и сможет спокойно продолжить сон 💤– « все в порядке , все так же , как было во время укладывания , ничего не изменилось » .🤗💤💤💤 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ в первые месяцы жизни малыша такие игрушки-компаньоны ему не так уж и нужны , а вот начиная с 6 ☝🏻месяцев использовать их очень даже рекомендуется . ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ что нужно иметь в виду , выбирая игрушку для сна ? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⭐️удобство вашей крохе должно быть комфортно обнимать и держать игрушку рядом с собой , а потому , размер выбирайте не слишком большой и не совсем маленький ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ ⭐️безопасность у игрушки , которая предназначена для сна не должно быть острых частей и деталей , которые могут поцарапать или навредить малышу . глазки , носики и прочие пластиковые детали должны быть очень хорошо закреплены , ведь малыш может захотеть их погрызть . лучше не рисковать и предложить ребенку игрушку без таких элементов , например , с вышитой мордочкой . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⭐️экологичность вы должны быть уверены в том , что материалы , из которых сделана игрушка , безопасны , а их наполнитель и красители безвредны . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⭐️цвета обходите стороной яркие расцветки . игрушка , которая предназначена для засыпания должна успокаивать , а не вызывать бурю эмоций . пастельные , приглушенные кофетные тона – то , что нужно ! ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ а какие у вас или вашего ребенка ассоциации на засыпание ? ♥️♥️♥️♥️♥️♥️⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀

lemma_filter: хотите , чтобы ребенок поскорее уснул ? ☺️ после 4 месяцев сон ребенка меняется . теперь начинают действовать ассоциации на засыпание . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ 💤ассоциации на засыпание – это условия , которые помогают человеку уснуть . привычная подушка , способ укутаться одеялом перед сном , любимая поза.☕️🍫 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀ игрушка , « спящая » рядом с ребенком , тоже является ассоциацией на засыпание . она находится рядом с малышом при засыпании , остается в кроватке на всю ночь . 🙂⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ при пробуждении ребенок обнаружит ее рядом с собой и сможет спокойно продолжить сон 💤– « все в порядке , все так же , как было во время укладывания , ничего не изменилось » .🤗💤💤💤 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀ в первые месяцы жизни малыша такие игрушки-компаньоны ему не так уж и нужны , а вот начиная с 6 ☝🏻месяцев использовать их очень даже рекомендуется . ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ что нужно иметь в виду , выбирая игрушку для сна ? text:
leadership development scholarships now available

building on the significant developmental momentum achieved during #100daysforchange, women & leadership australia is administering a national initiative to support the development of female leaders across australia’s sports sector. 
the initiative is providing women with grants of between $3,000 and $7,000 to enable participation in a range of leadership development programs. 
the scholarship funding is provided with the specific intent of providing powerful and effective development opportunities for women in the industry; however the funding is strictly limited and has to be allocated prior to the end of 2018.

expressions of interest 
find out more and register your interest by completing the expression of interest form here prior to december 7, 2018: 
www.wla.edu.au/funding1

text:
the thought was to wait till next year to start our projects as a foundation. but there are women and girls who have been suffering from abuses and the effects hoping for a glimpse of hope and someone who at least understands and will believe them. waiting would mean leaving them to hurt till next year...no.
.
.
with our project, rescue the girl child, we will be visiting primary and secondary schools all over nigeria to educate female students about sexual abuse, child trafficking and other forms of abuse that can affect them. with this, we want to get to meet girls who are victims and offer them help in the form of counseling and by partnering with other organizations, get them legal help too.
.
.
our first tour will be next month, november 2018. our target is 20 schools within lagos and ogun states.
.
.
rescue the girl child tour needs partnership (most important), volunteering and donations to take it further. our target is to reach out to girls in all schools in nigeria.
.
.
to partner with us, volunteer, or make a donation, send an email to admin@thehealedwoman.org or call +2347069403717
.
.

text:
tired of playing the victim card? here are a few faux pas you should avoid to be able to lead a happy, ignorant lifestyle. . 
1. don't have an opinion, but don't be unopinionated. 
2. don't have sex, but also don't be a prude.
3. don't hide your skin, but don't flaunt it
4. don't drink, but don't be a spoilsport. 
5. don't go out, but don't be a loner.
6. don't be chatty, but don't be an introvert.
7. don't wear make up, but don't be dull. 
8. don't be humorless, but also don't laugh too much.
9. don't be fat, but don't be skinny. 
10. don't be a housewife, but don't have a career. 
11. don't be, but also don't not be.

follow these simple steps and you'll never be able to play the victim card.
if none of these seem to work, clearly you are the problem. #metoo
.

text_retweet:
about vulnerability, rage, art, and speaking truth and power from our darkest souls.  pls read. #repost @bmoreart ・・・
did you know the autobiography behind this painting?? “gentileschi (1593-1653) was an exceptional artist. she was the first woman to be accepted into florence’s prestigious accademia delle arti del disegno, and caravaggio’s only female follower. she was raped, when she was 17, by her painting tutor, agostino tassi. when tassi refused to marry her (the only way to restore her reputation), her father took him to court. the young gentileschi testified against her rapist and endured torture to prove her honesty. tassi was sentenced to exile, though the punishment was not enforced.

in the wake of the rape and trial, gentileschi made two paintings of judith cutting off her enemy’s head. both are intensely physical, and the second is especially gory; you can almost feel the resistance of flesh to blade. scholars have noted that judith looks a lot like gentileschi, and holofernes a lot like tassi, making the paintings self-portraits of a rape victim’s revenge. during and after the kavanaugh confirmation hearings — in which the judge denied dr. ford’s accusations against him — people shared images of the artworks with and without comment. beyond the rage was a hunger for interpretations of sexual assault from the point of view of survivors.” excerpt from female artists are grappling with sexual violence in their work by @jilnotjill in the @nytimes #femaleartists #rape #metoo #artemisiagentileschi #nytimes #artreview #bmoreart

text:
the one with sexual harrassment!
i respect women! i genuinely do! i respect the #metoo mome......
oh! god i am genuinely scared of talking about this!
i had written a big caption but deleted it because i really don't know how some of you might take it. #metoo moment also gave rise to a horrible phenomenon of "defaming" so i really don't want to be the person going through that. if someone even remotely disagrees with my opinion i am fucked.. there will some people taking screenshot of this. and put up a story. people start saying things, they start judging.
some people will obviously ask me to elaborate about my opinion and try to understand what i am trying to say but very few of them.
let's not use the power of social media to defame somebody let's try and make it a platform to raise awareness about the situation and how one can protect themselves from it and  how you should deal with it rather than just triggering a debate out of it! so let's not screenshot and defame people but screenshot and raise an awareness.
.
.
.
.
.
.
ps: you are not a victim for sharing your story. you are a survivor setting the world on fire with your truth. and you never know who will need your light, your warmth and your courage
-alex elle
.

.
.
.
.
.

text:

1) those who understand this
2) those who haven't found it yet
3) those who refuse to allow themselves to experience it

text:
#metoo 
and no! i'm not sorry. you should be sorry for making me feel like an object. in a public bus, in a mall, in a market full of people, in places where god lives his thoughts, in every other corner of the world!
women go through a lot of sexual harassment. touched without her consent, labelled without her content, judged for her own solicitation! but, my body my choice! 
you are nobody to dictate me how i'm supposed to live my life. 
and it isn't only a woman who goes through this dreadful phase, there are men out there who went through hell because some a*****e couldn't keep his/her hands to himself/herself!
sending power to you all! sending love to you all! don't give up. if you are reading this, you have survived. you are the hero of your story.
🖤🖤🖤🖤🖤🖤

text:
"and then the princess found herself locked in a tower surrounded by a stinky moat with crocodiles and a huge scary dragon guarding the door," read the mother, with her eyes wide and voice deep.

then, she made a sad face and continued softly, "so, the poor princess waited and waited for her prince to come--" *"but, why was she waiting for the prince, mumma?!"*
asked the little girl, impatiently.

the mother added, "to come and save her, silly." "but, mumma, why did she need a prince to save her?" the girl asked again. "uhh... hmm..." the mother was at a loss of words.

the little girl said proudly, "if it were me, instead of waiting for years and years for a prince, i would have tamed the dragon and flew out of the window." i would have rescued myself." she discarded the book and walked away, "this princess is stupid." the mother whispered with a broad smile, "i guess it is time to rewrite the fairy tales." modernfairytales

lets teach our daughters to be self sufficient n independent rather than waiting for a prince or a miracle to happen!

text:
#metoo - post 1
.
it’s disheartening to see many people question & put down women who didn’t speak up when they were exploited in the past. i read a forward by a known writer that called these victims cowards. that’s despicable!
.
it’s not easy to call out perpetrators & have your entire life come under the radar in a country that anyhow shames the victim in most cases.
.
the pic above is from my college days in south delhi. i was as outgoing, moofat & way more argumentative than i am now. in my 3rd year, i worked part time as a spoken english language instructor & taught at various branches in ncr. one time, i was assigned a 630 am batch in gurgaon. so i’d teach early morning & head back at 930 am by bus straight to college.
.
one day, a guy sitting next to me started feeling up the back of my legs. i wasn’t dressed in short or western clothes, tho that shouldn’t matter at all! i was in a kurta with trousers since i taught ‘students’ way older than i & wanted to look mature. the bus was packed & this guy would have gotten thrashed had i said anything.
.
but i froze! my brain kept telling me to push his hand away or speak up but my body didn’t move. i got off at my home stop & took a bath immediately.
.
i was exactly the kind of girl you’d assume would slap a guy across his face for misbehaving. but i didn’t!
.
this has happened to most of us when we were young. mine is not even a serious case because ‘itna toh sabke saath hota hai’. that’s the sad unfortunate reality!
.
what people don’t realise is that in all kinds of cases of sexual exploitation; shock, fear & authority play a big part. would you say a rape was consensual if the woman didn’t fight back?
.
yes, some false cases are probably coming up but that doesn’t discount the actual real past cases of me too that are higher in number & the situation is exactly what it claims to be.
.
that’s the focus of me too! there is strength in numbers & it lends support & courage! but we as a society are conditioned to question a girls intentions/behaviour. let’s consciously try & end that cycle! stop judging! let’s do better! let’s be better!❤️
____________________
#notashamed #metooindia #womenforwomen #raisingkarma

the pic above is from my college days in south delhi. i was as outgoing, moofat & way more argumentative than i am now. in my 3rd year, i worked pa time as a spoken english language instructor & taught at various branches in ncr. one time, i was assigned a 630 am batch in gurgaon. so i’d teach early morning & head back at 930 am by bus straight to college.

text: despite the spectacle of those who think they are in power, spending tax payer money to further promote themselves and are oblivious to the beauty around them, who scream instead of listen, who lie and manipulate to improve themselves but not the collective, those who replace morality with bribes, there is this generation... these young  woman and men who inspire me to be better and stronger... these young woman who are thoughtful consumers and care about others, young woman who are growing up knowing they have a voice that deserves to be heard, and ears who are willing to listen to all sides and whose independence is a virtue not a fault. these young woman and men are the light that helps me feel ok, who view the world as an opportunity to help others not just themselves. we all support and protest in our own way, today we chose to bask in the warmth of the sun and hike a mountain, and view the spectacle of anger from a viewpoint of peace and gentleness, but do not for one second discount that as weakness. we chose the light and quiet today because that is what felt right today. we chose to have deep conversations and political discourse in a respectful way. politicians could learn a lot from these young woman... if only they would take the time to listen to someone who isn’t throwing them money. i am proud of these young woman for being who they are. i am hopeful because they care about the earth, the things they purchase, the way they treat others and their empowerment- they will change this world. watch them.  #nomoreanger #startlistening #reallylisten #theywillvotesoon #theyarewatching #metoo #theyarelistening #imtiredofbeingquiet #yesthosearedollsnotrealbabies

text:
tw: sexual trauma
• • • 
i cried at work today. i advocated for a therapy client of mine who was sexually assaulted last week and i was disappointed by the invalidating responses of some of my colleagues. one of my colleagues noted that calling my client to provide skills coaching and support since she has not been able to leave her house to get to therapy was “non-adherent to dbt,” to which i replied, “i don’t care.” sexual trauma is already so minimized and invalidated. as mental health providers, we can do better than that. 
not once did i question whether i would continue to provide support. my only question is how i can best provide support on my client’s healing journey. 
for a while now i’ve been noticing the shortcomings of a lot of evidence-based therapies to meet the needs of my clients, who generally present with multiple complex, interpersonal, and sexual traumas. i’ve been tying in pieces of knowledge and wisdom i’ve discovered in my magic practices and am continuing to research, brainstorm, practice, and allowing my intuition to guide me. my spread tonight provided some much needed validation and assurance that i’m on the right track. one thing i know for sure is that i will continue to fight for those who have experienced sexual trauma. 
in fighting for them, i am also fighting for myself.

text:
the other day i was in class and the kids started talking about sexual assualt and domestic violence. it was brought up by a few boys, "why don't they just tell someone or report it?" the thing is we can't always report it no matter how much we want to. people don't realized when this happens the victim is threatened, scared, muniplulated, etc.  the best i can describe it is, someone comes into your house with a loaded gun. you're scared for your life but you hide. the person finds you and have you at gunpoint what do you do? do you run knowing you won't get away or do you stay there for a safer route? 1 ends ur life right away the 2nd gives you a chance. that's house victims feel. sometimes we are also afraid of what people will say and who will leave and all the judgement. you can't really speak unless you put yourself in someone else's shoes. we would report it if we felt safe and we have to move at our own pace so if you know someone that's been effected just be patient with them and let them just go at their own pace because forcing them will make them close off. 
#mystory #sexualassualt #pain #metoo #breakingthesilence #domesticviolence #awareness #yournotalone

text: shamed. for making life choices. this happens a lot to me. my choice of becoming a pornographer. my choice to expose my naked body. my choice to expose my sexuality. my choice to expose the act of sex. shamed. forever shamed by my choices. i do not speak much about what my career choice has brought me in regards to how i am perceived not only in the world but also in the trans community. the hateful emails. the comments on social media. the many shows that call to hire me and “love what you are doing” only to get a call back “ sorry corporate won’t sign off on you” without any detailed information. why? because even they are ashamed to admit that i will not get hired for that role because of my very outspoken positive stance on sex and sexuality. so even though i am very successful in my chosen career path there are aspects of it that i still get shamed for. what does this say to me? it says that i am so happy i chose this career because you will not shame me for my choices just because you have hangups about sex. you will not shame me for being very outspoken about my vagina. what it says to me is that you see me and you hear me! that’s why i choose to stay in the field of trans sexuality. you will not shame me out you have shamed me to speak louder and create more products that will help my community learn to love their bodies the way i have! so thank you for reminding me how important standing up for what you believe in is! i hope you learn this lesson from me and never let anyone shame you out of your passion! ❤️tranpa

text:
i'm so over the notion that posting "sexy selfies" as a woman makes you appear less competent.  and i'm dedicated to tracking where i feel this messaging still embedded in my programing - and actively purging myself of this patriarchal control tactic. .
.
i saw a study circulating again recently (from 2014) that has a takeaway along these lines. not surprisingly, the study found that it was women who were judging each other as less competent. this is sister wounding - where we police each other and fear our own power as holograms of the divine. .
.
if you are a person who isn’t willing to look at this indoctrinated script honestly and compassionately - then you are probably not an appropriate person for me to work with at this point in my career - because now i'm only interested in working with people who are ready to break down the internalized taboos that keep us in boxes. i'm only interested in working with people who are ready to be free. .
.
because, news flash - i am a sexual, sensual creature. 
this is my birth right, as it is yours. 
i have autonomy over my body and my image. 
i get a lot of pleasure out of noodling with nerdy apps and posting this cosmic pic of me and my stargate boobs with my fuzzy pit hair. and adding some of my witchy tunes to the mix to make it extra dreamy vibes. it's fun and playful. i'm happy to share this less serious, more creative and wild side of my personality with y'all! .
.
i'm also really good at my job and many other things i decide to put my energy towards.

text:
thank you @themuchomama for the #whatiwanttotellyou hashtag.
what i want to tell my younger self:
🔹not everyone is going to like you. that's okay. you're passionate and loud. compassionate and goofy. dramatic and sometimes short tempered. even when you're almost 30, you still let some of that insecurity sink back in. shut it out. you don't have to be like everyone else to be cool. life isn't a freaking popularity contest! you are going to be very disappointed if you allow your self esteem to be tied up in other people's opinions of you.
🔹#metoo dammit and don't for one second feel like you have to give something away, so it won't be taken from you. that's not fair, and i'm sorry. and i love you. and i know it's hard.
🔹i know it sucks being the big little sister. it sucks having stretch marks before you're a teenager. it sucks having acne and bad hair. but one day you'll love your body, your curves, your gigantic smile, and your thick hair! there's something to be said about that ugly ducking, beautiful butterfly story after all, and one day you won't be ashamed to publicly call yourself beautiful.
🔹boys are stupid. stop wasting your time on them. stop trying to change them. you deserve so much better than these little boys you're chasing. don't settle because you have low self esteem. enjoy being young and having girlfriends! stop looking for a relationship and spend more time getting to know who you are!
🔹stop being mean to your mom. she's going to be your best friend one day, and you'll regret trying to push her away.
🔹school spirit is not for dorks. you'll spend your entire adult  life in high school. (scary, huh?) get involved. make friends. dress up for theme weeks and go to football games even if you don't understand sports. but quit the band. good decision. don't stop taking piano lessons though.
🔹go to therapy. best decision you make in college. trust me. you need it.
🔹don't change a thing at 21. you'll never regret how you spent that carefree year of your life. you grow a lot that year.
🔹marry that man. he gives you a child, who makes you a mom. that's the most fulfilling, purest, & beautiful thing you'll ever experience. he's your purpose.

name: The Daily Ember
pre_proc_tweet:
there is no doubt this moment calls for a powerful mobilization against the trump administration and the ruling-class, white-supremacist interests it represents. but establishment democrats' strategy of hitching their “resistance” campaign to russiagate is misguided and dangerous. by demanding trump prove he’s tough on russia, the same democrats who warn that trump is dangerous and unhinged are asking him to oversee an even more bellicose foreign policy. the net effect has been to push the u.s. government to take a more confrontational stance toward russia and other geopolitical foes and—ultimately—expand its military empire.
whatever one thinks about the aims and scope of russian interference, the evidence is undeniable: democrats’ overwhelming focus on russia has led directly to a significan not—and measurable—military buildup. the $716 billion national defense authorization act (ndaa) for 2019 is massive, marking an $81 billion increase over 2017 (adjusted for inflation). the bill explicitly targets russia and china. from the outset, lawmakers on both sides of the aisle cited the threat of russian interference to argue in favor of the ndaa. rep. adam smith (d-wash.), the ranking democrat on the house armed services committee, gushed, “this bill continues the absolutely critical work of pushing back against president putin.” smith, who earlier that month called for an impeachment investigation of trump, appeared eager and willing to hand the president a giant check for war.
bipaisan lawmakers handed a major victory to trump by passing the defense bill, which includes $6.5 billion to fully fund the “european deterrence initiative” to build the military capabilities of european states near russia. the legislation also instructs secretary of defense james mattis to conduct a feasibility study on whether a “permanently stationed united states army brigade combat team in poland would enhance deterrence against russian aggression.”

text:
with the #metoo campaign currently going around, i feel like i need to share something. if you are a survivor of childhood sexual abuse, there is something you can do to help you on your journey to heal. 
the younique foundation offers a free retreat to survivors of childhood sexual abuse. they don't force younique products on you, they don't even use our products in the makeover and photoshoot because they don't want there to be even an ounce of room for someone to say they have the wrong intentions. this foundation has one purpose, and one purpose only: to help you heal. 
no business. no sales. nothing except opportunities for you to rediscover your self-worth and heal. you are powerful beyond measure. 
if you want to know more, please check out www.youniquefoundation.org, where you can read more and apply to attend the retreat or contact me. 
#nomore1in4 #reclaimhope  #ibelieveyou

text:
the story goes like this
ii:

i went to the hospital the morning after i was sexually assaulted because i felt like it was the right thing to do. my gut said “just go.” those 400 plus episodes of law and order svu taught me something. first, though, i called the national sexual assault helpline [800-656-hope (4673)]. i needed to know if going to the hospital meant i’d have to press charges. i wasn’t ready to think about pressing charges. i only wanted to feel safe.

you not need to press charges if you go to the hospital for a rape kit. a police office will show up before the testing and documenting and examining are through and you’ll file a report, but you do not need to decide to press charges at that time. you do not need to do anything you do not want to do. the evidence will be gathered and how you proceed is your choice. it’s no one else’s.
•
•
•
•
•

text:
i really enjoyed the 2018 champions of justice dinner sponsored by the mississippi center for justice. they honored holmes county own, robert g. clark, the first african american elected to the legislature since reconstruction . they also honored carol penick who had me in tears as she, for the first time in public, shared her #metoo story! 
state representative robert g. clark, jr. was born on october 3, 1929 in ebenezer, mississippi to robert g. clark, sr. and julia ann clark. clark attended holmes county training school in durant, mississippi. clark went on to attend jackson state college, where he received his b.a. degree in 1952. he then earned his m.s degree in administration and educational services from michigan state university in 1959.
clark served as a teacher in the holmes county public school system and area private schools for fifteen years. in 1966, clark began his career in politics and was elected to a position in the holmes county community action program. the following year, he was elected to the state of mississippi house of representatives as the first black representative of the twentieth century. while serving in the house of representatives, clark served as chair of the house education committee, the house management committee, the house ethics committee. he also held a seat on the house rules committee and served as vice chairman for the apportionment and elections committee. in 1979, in addition to serving in the mississippi house of representatives, he served as a teaching fellow at the john f. kennedy school of government at harvard university. clark was credited for the 1982 education reform act, which significantly reformed mississippi’s educational system. in 1992, he was elected as house of representatives speaker pro tem, a position he would be re-elected to in 1996 and 2000. clark was also a senior ranking member of mississippi’s legislative black caucus. in 2003, clark retired from the house representatives and began lecturing at mississippi valley state university.clark was honored by the state of mississippi for his years of service. in 2003, june 27th was dedicated as robert g. clark, jr. day by an official state of ms.
name: Edelia "Dr. Jay" Carthan

text:
priscilla rainey reportedly wants the game thrown behind bars.

for almost three years, the game has been caught up in a neverending sexual assault case against priscilla rainey. rainey was a contestant on “she’s got game,” a reality show that was created for the game to find his new romantic match. she filed a lawsuit against the rapper in 2015, writing that he had sexually assaulted her by forcefully reaching under her dress and rubbing her bare vagina and buttocks with his hand. rainey previously won a $7 million judgment against game but she believes that since he’s been skipping out on court dates, he should face the consequences behind bars.

according to the blast, rainey has filed legal documents to combat the game as he’s reportedly pushing to have his warrant dismissed. the alleged victim is accusing game of failing to explain a number of large cash deposits he’s received over the last few months, which would be relevant to their case. his marijuana business and several entertainment companies have gone largely unspoken for and rainey wants a better understanding of why he’s been holding back information. he was previously ordered to hand over his bank statements and rainey says that he has not cooperated completely.

as of now, the warrant is still active. rainey claims that she has not seen a single penny from the previous judgment, which game is fighting as well. get the full tea at www.itskenbarbie.com #thegame #hateitorloveit #shesgotgame #losangelesconfidential #jayceontaylor #entertainment #metoo #entertainmentnews #gossip #celebrities #celebrityblogger #kenbarbie #itskenbarbie

text:
actress radhika apte expressed her full support to the sexual harassment survivors, who are calling out their alleged tormentors under the #metoo campaign.

while interacting with the media at the launch of new collection of daniel wellington watches as their brand ambassador, radhika on wednesday hoped that the film industry would come up with an "equal and genderless" system to tackle any kind of harassment cases.

radhika has been associated with kwan entertainment -- one of the biggest celebrity management agencies in india -- whose founder has been sacked after four aspiring actresses anonymously accused him of seeking sexual favours.

asked whether she will disassociate herself with the celebrity management agency, radhika said: "i am completely and closely in contact with them. the people who are associated with kwan have helped me and i have a great relationship with them. they are taking all required action as we all support the (#metoo) movement." #india #world #usa #metoo #picoftheday #radhikaapte #bollywoodmemes #bollywood #glamour #harrassment #misbehave #police #tragedy #disturbing #thegulftoday
