text:
primas is coming to theatres in québec starting september 28th. 
the film is about rocio and aldana, two of the most inspiring people i have met in my life, whose story is as uplifting as it is heartbreaking. 
they have touched thousands of hearts as we have been blessed with a tremendous festival tour.

one of the people who were touched by their story was our friend meghann jones, a gifted jeweller from montreal.  she has managed to capture the inward/outward scarring/strength that these young women embody. 
she has made these stunning pendants and bracelets that i am happy to tell you we are now selling, online and at some select screenings of the film. 100% of the profits from the money we raise selling these pieces will go towards local organisation mouvement contre le viol et l'inceste - a tremendous support group that fights against some of the systematic causes behind sexual violence, rape, incest and the marginalization of immigrant communities, as well as supporting the survivors of these crimes. 
please buy a necklace, come see the film, contact us to book a screening in your home town, and say enough to all forms of sexual violence and violence against women. 
#basta.

text: finished a second book today with war on peace by ronan farrow of #metoo fame. this book highlights the breakdown of the state department, and more importantly the decline of america’s capacity to engage in diplomacy. this book uses about half of its pages to use the trials and errors in afghanistan and pakistan to show just how this failure has harmed and weakened the us. if you have an interest in the development of american foreign policy in the last 30 years, this is a great place to start. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ #waronpeace #ronanfarrow #wwnorton #book #books #bookstagram #bookish #bookstagrammer #bookworm #booksbooksbooks #booksofig #booksofinstagram #booksofinsta #foreignpolicy #americandiplomacy #billclinton #georgewbush #barrackobama #donaldtrump #statedepartment #pakistan #afghanistan

text:
cw: i’m about to talk about sexual assault. so if you wanna scroll past my words, i understand. but i’m not writing in terms of detail. but to call attention to it.
.
we live in a world where sexual assault is merely seen as a joke. where womxn are ignored when speaking out, where men are shunned by society for speaking out, being completely ignored. like when terry crews came out at the peak of the #metoo movement. there was hardly even any conversation about his strength & bravery for coming out! where were we as a society to support him? we weren’t. there are cases where men are wrongly accused for rape, and i can’t fuck with that.
.
sexual assault is not a joke. sexual assault is not about sex.
it’s about power.
power over someone’s sexuality is one of the ultimate ways of accessing power. to hurt someone in such a vulnerable way, so intimately, creates lifelong stains for the survivor.
.
as survivors, we react differently to the world around us. we have different ideals when it comes to sexual relationships.
we feel a need to control the way we’re sexually perceived.
sometimes these feelings lead to promiscuity, erotic modeling, identity issues, need for approval, lack of sexuality, feeling inadequate sexually, never having healthy sexual relationships, never wanting to be with a man ever again. (there are men that don’t want to be with womn that do this too)
.
let’s talk about sex. let’s talk about healthy sex. harmful sex. using sex as void for other issues we are facing in our lives. let’s talk about how much it hurts to be a sexual assault survivor. let’s create an open forum where we can feel empowered by surviving and moving towards a goal in our society to be open about these things. to assert power through sexual abuse is not okay. let’s talk about it.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
loading and unloading boxes, making 34 phone calls in a single day, driving through traffic to get to an event on a daily basis, technical glitches in the website, and a bunch of other things that i don't like about my work...but you know what? i wouldn't trade it for anything in the world because i am in love with what i do! there may be aspects of your work that you don't like, but if your work brings you a life of joy then it's all worth it. keep things in perspective.

text: i wrote this poem to myself after i was drugged and attacked by a bartender. i was so terrified of every little thing, i imagined what my love would say to me if we were still together, he always called me little bird, i felt kinda silly writing this to myself but for whatever reason it made me feel better. evil can be omnipresent in this world which means we ourselves need to be the light to inspire others. i believe goodness is contagious and we have the power to make this world a more beautiful place for every race, religion, skin color, ethnicity, ideology, witches, everyone #poetry #metoo #metoomovement

text:
“shameless feminine”
🌼
beloved,
i come to you now, 
pulled by your sleeping scarlet dreams,
your flowers of yearning,
your earth’s turning,
🌼
that i may reach into this vessel
—beyond feast of ghost and
pain possessing pleasure—
and bend my love into you,
become your trestle,
🌼
till you rise upon my kisses
and your light breaks only into dawn
— never a slave
to their empty grave
no more.
- rh
🌼🌼🌼
📷 by @kamil_vojnar_art and @trevillionimages 🙏🏻
.

.
though you may not quite understand this poem without having read my chapter, i felt called to share it anyway. perhaps, it has a little medicine for you. .
i love you all,
💘 rebecca

text:
taylor swift sweetrocks inspiring woman⠀
⠀
taylor swift is one of the world's leading contemporary recording artists, she is known for narrative songs about her personal life, which have received widespread media coverage.⠀
swift moved to nashville, tennessee at the age of 14 to pursue a career in country music. she signed with the label big machine records and became the youngest artist ever signed by the sony/atv music publishing house. ⠀
taylor is one of the best-selling music artists of all time, having sold more than 40 million albums—including 27.8 million in the us—and 130 million single downloads. as a songwriter, she has received awards from the nashville songwriters association and the songwriters hall of fame, and was included in rolling stone's 100 greatest songwriters of all time in 2015. she is also the recipient of 10 grammys, one emmy, 23 billboard music awards, and 12 country music association awards, and she holds six guinness world records. she has appeared in time's 100 most influential people in the world (2010 and 2015) and forbes' lists of top-earning women in music (2011–2015), 100 most powerful women (2015), and celebrity 100 (2016). her inclusion in the third of these made her the youngest woman on the list, and she ranked first in celebrity 100.⠀
⠀
taylor swift, thank you for being an inspiring woman!⠀
⠀

text: this is a goofy, up-close and personal picture. but, it shows my true smile which is something that i’ve missed dearly. after much thought, i’ve decided that i need to be honest with the people in my life. i am a survivor... i am part of the #metoo movement. i have survived one sexual assault, one dv relationship and within the past year, i was drugged and raped. as appealing as saying nothing about my situation is, my story and my voice can potentially help someone in my life. i’ve struggled with my reality for 8 years since my first occurrence...but i’ve survived, and i’m surviving. life’s been rough lately as my trial gets closer. almost a year ago, i moved to a completely different state and left behind my whole family, all my friends and my whole support system as i knew it. it’s challenging to say the least but liberating as fuck. #metoo #survivor #oregon #livingmytruth #mytruth #speakyourtruth

text:
there’s so much to take from this profile on tarana burke, founder of the *actual* #metoo movement. one of the parts that hit me the most is her talking about how we have to move beyond just trauma dumping and expecting folks to do something; they won’t. statistics about sexual assault are readily available in many places but people ignore it just like they do survivors. so what now?

her insistence that we must move to a space of providing resources to survivors first and for most, is something that informed my latest video (link in bio). cuz like, yes, believe survivors, but what’re you doing for them? what beyond consuming survivor trauma are you tangibly doing? what’re we doing so that we can reduce the rates of sexual assaults? are we educating ourselves; others? are we being critical of the media we consume and how it might perpetuate rape culture?

burke’s emphasis on attacking systemic failures is also important. we should be doing more to educate folks on things like the uselessness of rape kits and the faulty logic of even needing witnesses for a private crime. and on and on. but most of all: we should be angry at a system that does not make it easy for survivors to survive.
.
full article:
https://www.nytimes.com/2018/10/15/arts/tarana-burke-metoo-anniversary.html
.

text:
sexual #coercion is unwanted #sexual activity that happens when you are pressured, tricked, threatened, or forced in a nonphysical way. coercion can make you think you owe #sex to someone. it might be from someone who has power over you, like a teacher, landlord, or a boss. it might be from a partner or #spouse. no person is ever required to have sex with someone else.

sexual coercion is a form of #sexualassault. 
sexual activity is only legal when both parties consent. consent is defined in canada’s criminal code in s. 273.1(1), as the voluntary agreement to engage in the sexual activity in question. the law focuses on what the person was actually thinking and feeling at the time of the sexual activity. sexual touching is only lawful if the person affirmatively communicated their #consent, whether through words or conduct. silence or passivity does not equal consent.

original post:

you could replace any genders in here and it would still be true, but this specifically is very important💪❤️ shared from @the_democratic_hippie

#metoo #sexualassault #consentmatters

text:
so after 4 years of waiting for this tattoo. i finally got it.  the armored bear i became over my battle scars. since the day i was born my dad called me bear. after years of bullying, abuse,  and stuff that puts me in the ' #metoo ' movement. i self harmed and attempted at my own life. somehow i made through it all. i became an armored bear. i decided to put a representation of my strength over something dark from my past. 
and i couldn't be happier with it.

text:
ah yes... 23 year old heather. #nyc rooftop chillin' in june. i had an amazing job, surrounded by amazing women, young, free and so, so, so happy... cant you tell?
.
what if i told you this was also me at the absolute lowest point in my life? i was lost, hurting, and extremely self-destructive. the next 13 months after this picture was taken were the hardest and scariest months of my life.
but i'm still here.
.
i still carry around a lot of emotional baggage and trauma that i try to chip away at daily. i sometimes slip back into the same head space that kept me under water for so long. i still have a mean temper at times, and lord only knows the next time i'll burst into tears.
but i'm still here.
.
depression doesn't have a mold. we can't pick [it] out in the crowd. [it] comes and goes as [it] pleases. [it] changes as [it] moves from person to person. [it] never leaves the same mark twice. [it]'s an absolute bitch. [it]'s real. [it]'s fierce. and [it] never fully goes away.
but i'm still here.
.
those of us who have danced with the devil  know that it is no easy feat to get to a place where we can just function with the outside world, but we do it. we walk again. we smile and laugh deep belly laughs again. we venture back into gyms, and into nature, and taste fruits and veggies again. we kiss, we hug, we make love again. we bounce back and we pick up the pieces of our lives that were once shattered on the ground. and when we feel [it] lurking near, we buckle down, embrace, breathe, reach out and remind ourselves:
we are still here.
.
be present. ask someone how they are doing. reach out. connect. spread the lōve.
.
🌿💜

text:
i wish i could give a shout out to whoever made this graphic, but alas i can’t. that is me (lower right) as a kid. as females, and moreover as a female dancer, i was taught to scrutinize my body daily. this was part of an art project i made while working with an amazing healer/therapist, marta luzim, of primal healing and art. 
i’ve been so busy that i haven’t been posting too much, and for some reason i am putting this out there. 
i’m so grateful for my growth and the part of me that has had the desire to work on myself. 
here’s to all women, here’s to vulnerability, here’s to accepting ourselves and here’s to asking for help when we need it.

text:
no one has walked in my shoes. no one has felt my pain. no one can see the pain i still have burning inside me. people say let go, close the door, just forget about it. if only it was that simple. it has been so long since i've felt like myself. who am i supposed to be? everyone tells me what i should be doing with my life, but they don't see the truth about me. it's not all sunshine and rainbows. its hard work. fixing myself. healing myself. these things take time. i don't know how long it will take me. i'm still trying my best. it hurts because it matters. people won't see the pain they have caused you. i can admit my faults. can you say the same for yourself? would you stand up for someone who has been hurt, or stand behind people who are blinded by what is right in front of them? i would never cause the pain the has been caused to me. i am healing myself and justice will be served. its okay to not be okay. #metoo
.

text:
growing up, i got very clear messages about my hair. white trash. dirty looking. chaotic. not curly enough to be pretty, not straight enough to just let it dry and have it look nice. the goal, instead, was blonde and straight and that's how i wore my hair for forever. if there was a chance my photo would be taken, my hair was straightened. i spent tons of money to keep it blonde enough, and spent tons of time to keep it straight. i did this for years and years and years. i bought my first really nice straightener from the salon across the street from the restaurant i worked at in orlando about 12 years ago, and i went to town.

ah, 12 years ago. right around the time of my assault. is this why i straightened my hair? was i wearing it curly the night before (and thus the morning of) my assault? was this just another way i tried to blend all the way in to the background after surviving that? could be. or maybe one boy said matter-of-factly that my curls made me look trashy. either way, it's exhausting doing all of this for anyone other than myself.

i started wearing my hair curly again after i first started skydiving. the second i walked onto a dz (read: the second i met @maker_of_waves), i felt more free to be myself than i had anywhere else previously. i learned to let go of my straight hair rules for photo opps and embraced my natural texture. there was nothing more freeing that showing after a long day in the sky and not doing my hair after. i'd spend all weekend at the dz and drive into the agency on monday morning. one morning at work, i was told i needed to present "more female" if i wanted to be taken seriously in my career. i wasn't gonna wear a dress, so i busted the straightener back out.

on the #transcatalinatrail the second time in june, i wasn't straightening my hair, obviously. in fact, after i dunked myself in the ocean at parsons, i didn't even comb it. i just let it dry, let the curls form how they want, and let it ride. and i've been doing that every single day since.

i've been #hikingmyfeelings. on the tct, i started #reclaimingmybody. that includes my hair. this is me. wild and free. 💖🦄🌌 📸@freckled_wanderer

text:
white cliffs of dover in progress... 18/10/18

i have loved england, dearly and deeply, 
since that first morning, shining and pure, 
the white cliffs of dover i saw rising steeply

first attempt at painting on a canvas, as well as being handicapped by having only 4 colours to use. but i’m extremely delighted with the outcome.

inspiration came from my inner love for this beautiful land we get to call home and the current msm negative mood towards it.

the white cliffs of dover soar strong and tremendously. 
the greenish misty sky represents the jealousy the eu will feel when looking across at the uk, what they’ll see is that labour have won the next general election and one of founding fathers of euro scepticism and true brexiteer king corbyn is in power, turning the uk into a true socialist 3 day working week state with perfect human rights for everyone from your neighbour to your local butchers cat 🙌🏻🙌🏻🙌🏻 the birds represent... well i just like painting birds as they’re easy

text:
today i went to a networking meeting hoping to encounter like- minded people. instead what i encountered was a few minutes of subpar discussion followed by a hearty discussion of women, women's weight, fat women, etc. 
to say the least i was appalled, disgusted and saddened that fellow professional (yes, unfortunately i was the only woman in the company of men) would go to that level. 
a fellow realtor even went as far as telling the group how he used to approach "fat" women and ask them if they were pregnant - as a joke... i promptly got up and excused myself. yes, i left on a classy note, however i called the host of the meeting later on to let him know how i felt - disgusted, appalled, astonished, furious, etc.

this truly needs to stop. surely a professional group has more important things to discuss than whether or not a woman's stomach resembles a watermelon... #metoo #respect #professional #openinindiana #beyou #stayclassy

text:
sarah (@sowusu) shares her experiences on colourism and growing up with dark skin.✨
・・
i grew up being called “blick”, darkie which to me were all very derogatory terms. not only was my skin apparently too “dark” but my nose was also “too big” and my lips were referred to as “bubba lips” and “burger lips” just to name a few. funny that, because now i am often asked if i have had “lip injections” and told how “beautiful” my skin is from the very same people who once tried to push me into hating myself. now, melanin has almost become somewhat of a fashion “trend” and everyone wants to take full ownership of their melanin when this should have never been a “thing” in the first place. oh and please cut out the “you’re so pretty for a black/dark skin girl” it’s getting very boring now and it has never been a compliment. god created us all in his image which makes us all his masterpieces, from the whitest of snow to the darkest of night. people are arguing about the colour emoji people are using... this is very worrying. we’re all beautiful and it’s about time colourism stopped. seriously, it’s disgusting.” #ourwomensvoices
name: Our Women's Voices

text:
⭐me acting on mickey spillane's mike hammer tv series⭐
-
-✨#throwbackthursday this picture was taken right from the actual show.
-
-✨working with stacey keach was wonderful.
-
-✨he was a complete gentleman.
-
-✨i always had fun for the most part working in hollywood. but the #metoo movement is very real.
-
-✨i had quite a few experiences with executive's at major studios and television stations. where i was in a professional audition set up by my agent and they made sexual advances.
-
-✨back then there was no recourse or anyone in particular to turn to. i wasn't naive and have experienced this in other industries as well but i was still horrified and didn't participate in anyway.
-
-✨i was surprised back then the high level of executive's that were doing this. not just actor's who can be the worst. or b movie producers that did that all the time.
-
-✨i had one movie producer try nurmous times to get me to sleep with him for a role.
-
-✨i kept saying no. i'll never forget he said well if you don't sleep with anyone in hollywood you won't make it.
-
-✨i didn't even hesitate. i said "well i guess i won't make it then!"
-
-✨that put an end to that harassment. i'm sure had i did do that i would have got a lot further in my acting career.
-
-✨that just isn't who i am. i know a lot of actresses who did do that. i don't judge. i just hope that bringing awareness to this very real and serious situation gives other young women coming to hollywood a real chance.
-
-✨without having to go through what so many of us did.
-
-✨thank god not everyone in hollywood is that way. i know it seems like it but there are some real stand up people in the acting industry.
-

name: Marketing Coach
tweet_full:
⭐me acting on mickey spillane's mike hammer tv series⭐
-
-✨#throwbackthursday this picture was taken right from the actual show.
-
-✨working with stacey keach was wonderful.
-
-✨he was a complete gentleman.
-
-✨i always had fun for the most part working in hollywood. but the #metoo movement is very real.
-
-✨i had quite a few experiences with executive's at major studios and television stations. where i was in a professional audition set up by my agent and they made sexual advances.
-
-✨back then there was no recourse or anyone in particular to turn to. i wasn't naive and have experienced this in other industries as well but i was still horrified and didn't participate in anyway.
-
-✨i was surprised back then the high level of executive's that were doing this. not just actor's who can be the worst. or b movie producers that did that all the time.
-
-✨i had one movie producer try nurmous times to get me to sleep with him for a role.
-
-✨i kept saying no. i'll never forget he said well if you do not sleep with anyone in hollywood you will not make it.
-
-✨i didn't even hesitate. i said "well i guess i will not make it then!"
-
-✨that put an end to that harassment. i am sure had i did do that i would have got a lot further in my acting career.
-
-✨that just is not who i am. i know a lot of actresses who did do that. i do not judge. i just hope that bringing awareness to this very real and serious situation gives other young women coming to hollywood a real chance.
-
-✨without having to go through what so many of us did.
-
-✨thank god not everyone in hollywood is that way. i know it seems like it but there are some real stand up people in the acting industry.
-
-✨ i have stories that would make your toes curl. lol💯💯

text:
this 1797 “wife for sale” etching is “social satire.” but it wasn’t funny being a wife. in 1850 an english wife had no rights to the children she gave birth to. all her property passed to her husband on marriage. her wages belonged to her husband. she owned nothing  so didn’t make a will. women in the u.k. got parental rights equal to men in 1973 with the guardianship act. think about that for a minute ... then read my book to find out why! 🤔

text:
dear paxton,

a year ago, i wrote you a letter about the #metoo movement. since then, you’ve grown stronger…physically, mentally and emotionally. my promise to be your role model and to show you everyday how to respect, appreciate and treat women is more important now than it was then. i hope you grasp the gravitas of treating people equally and justly. your mom is brilliantly intelligent and an absolutely phenomenal human being. be like her. be better than me. be whoever you want to be as long as you treat people well. as you continue to progress into your own person, i need you to be the biggest advocate of humanity. together, we will lead by example so that future generations of brilliant and phenomenal women will never be victimized by the #metoo movement. #howiwillchange

love,
dad

text: ***update - taken!*** this striking design, called the fire rose unity survivor tattoo, was created by jacqueline lin. in her words, "it is made for and dedicated to survivors.  it is a unity symbol inspired by the loops of our dna structure and our universal infinity sign.  it combines inspiration from lady gaga's favorite flower, the white rose, to breathe life into an organic and growing symbol.  the final image embraces a fiery shape to give us power and strength everywhere we go." lady gaga and 50 men and women survivors of sexual abuse were tattooed with this image in solidarity and displayed it at the 2016 oscars.  we have one tattoo session for sale with david allen, the artist who originally tattooed lady gaga for that event.  this is a special gift as mr allen has a wait list of over two years.  please pm me directly with interest.  chicago sitting only.  100% of proceeds from this will benefit resilience, formerly rape victims advocates.

text:
ich hatte echt einen genialen abend  bei dita von teese der meine erwartungen übertraf. 💄
nichts boosted dein selbstvertrauen so wie sich zwei stunden lang frauen, in allen größen, formen, farben und alters, anzugucken die sich so selbstbewusst, wie ich es wohl noch nie vorher gesehen hab auf einer pompösen bühne vor einem ausverkauften saal so ästhetisch wie möglich, ihrer kleider entledigen. 💖
und so selbstbewusst und mit einem gigantischem lächeln verlies ich die show. das hielt auch noch ne weile an .... ziemlich genau bis ich zur sbahn ging. und dann wurde der weg nach hause echt immer unangenehmer. 
ich wurde noch nie in meinem leben so dreist angestarrt...
naja obwohl doch, als ich anfing keine bhs mehr zu tragen, aber das war eher immer so ein unglaubwürdiger blick ....
diesmal jedoch war es richtig eklig.
und ja ich wurde ausschließlich von männern aufs dümmste angegafft. 
zur info ich trug noch ne jacke drüber, zugeknöpft. 
ich seh auch so oft leute die ich attraktiv finde, gerade in berlin, und ich kriegs doch auch gebacken die nicht komplett hirnlos anzugaffen. 
von mir aus setz dich auch zu mir und sprich mich an wenn’s dich so juckt aber dich umzusetzen um nen besseren blick zu haben und andauern super auffällig über die schulter mich von oben bis unten zu mustern muss doch nicht sein. 
ich bin eigentlich ziemlich hart im nehmen und versuch mich auch nicht von viel stören zu lassen aber wenn mir leute so nen geilen abend doch ein bisschen versauen da hört’s auf. 🙅🏻‍♀️
das ist kein flirten ! 🚫
das ist kein kompliment ! 🚫
das ist nicht meine absicht ! 🚫
und selbst wenn
ist das nicht bei dir das zu entscheiden ! 🚫
fakt ist einfach ich geh mit nem scheiß gefühl und dem schlüssel in der faust nach hause !!! 🖕🏻
(auch wenn ich so nicht denken und handeln möchte passiert es manchmal einfach.)

text:
ok-- nows she's done. close up of the new profile edging. my submission for the "their names are not anonymous anymore" 40th anniversary show at @otwdirtyfranks. wish me luck! 
this work reflects on a phrase that has been used to manipulate me personally, to undermine my anger, sadness, and trauma. i thought i had to do what they said to be a "nice girl." well, i am not a nice girl and i don't give a fuck what you think. "i am not a nice girl," 18 x 18 in. vintage upholstery, hand embroidery, lace, polyfill.

text:
i am a survivor of sexual assault and an abusive relationship. and i am so proud of the woman i have become. it took time, but i got the help needed and realized i had to start healing to live a healthy life. my healing journey began almost four years ago and it is far from over. i will be honest saying that it definitely has not been the easiest but it has been well worth it. i know that every survivor deserves peace and healing. it is attainable, it is accessible and there are so many people who want to help you. you are not alone. and you do not have to carry this pain alone. no one is deserving of an abusive relationship. it’s not fair to have experienced these things, however it is in your control to make a change and help yourself! ❤️❤️❤️ http://sasaworldwide.org

text: this navratri when we all celebrated the power of womanhood and celebrated the fact good over evil always wins. we also witnessed stories of #metoo in the real world during navratri. the woman came out boldly to speak about the incidence they experienced and were shy to say about for many years but like maa durga all came out strong against the devil of sexual harassment. some stories real and some just made headlines. but in india, do we really understand the meaning of harassment ? is only sexual harassment an issue ? a woman who is independent or a woman who is a home maker might be harassed mentally, socially or may be morally too isn't that  a much bigger issue to #metoo. why just blame the people famous, why not help woman fight harassment that she might be facing in her daily life ? help her fight depression of getting harassed at work, home, by her children, by her in-laws or even by her husband? shouldn't that become a bigger moment / campaign to give strength to woman of middle class, service class who come under the pier pressure of societal taboos. give her the #metoo power to exercise her constitutional rights to speech, her constitutional right to expression. why only india is a country where we worship a goddess strengths and on the contrary she still has her everyday struggle to be appreciated, to get a status she deserves as part of a family. as a country we might be getting modern / digitalized but unfortunately in our minds we are still critical and typical of the woman who gave men their first heartbeat inside her. if the men in india are made to realise to start looking inside their family and start valuing the younger woman and the oldest one as one without any discretion i am certain of a much happier and #metoo free country. don't just stand in front of maa durga and ring bells. but respect womanhood around you. throw your false ego away. value the girls who leave their home to come to yours to make their own. value the birth of  a daughter in your house. in fact a woman should start helping another woman to gain courage. #metoo her to gain that strength to emerge a winner in her sorroundings wherever she goes.

text:
today, i want to honour our super-princess lea messier @leamessier. this seems like as good a time as any to talk #minibarleadingladies - i want to share some stories, some snappy opinions and some great advice from some of my favourite people in the world! follow along the hashtag - strong-willed content that we can reflect on, during the good times and the challenging moments. .
.
lea messier is a bright and shining star, growing up in quebec city by way of brittany, france, and now living in montreal. although events are her speciality, she loves being in the hospitality industry – both bartending and creating menus. with a question of what lea hopes to see over the next 3 years and 10 years in our industry, she says, “i love to see the concept of ‘drink less, drink better’. just like indulging in the food world, it’s better to enjoy smaller portions of what you like, in an effort to protect your body, both physically & mentally. moderation is key. it’s our duty as ambassadors of the food and beverage industry to help our guests, friends & colleagues drink better, and drink responsibly – enjoy a more balanced lifestyle.” what you need to know, is that lea is charismatic, brilliant and obsessed with science fiction and hero flicks – like thor, star trek and beyond. .
.
lea needs to describe herself in a few words, we demand it, as she’s such a strong personality, and this is what she says, "my grandmother pierrette was born with the happiness gene, and she passed it to my mother, who passed it to me – she told me ‘lea, the goal in life is to be happy, always keep this in mind’ and i do. everyday. i am happy – that’s the word that best describes me.” #bitteredsling #beboldforchange

text: world conflict resolution day 18. 10 18. shared today with like minded friends/mediators...talking about the notion of 'truth' both in the mediation world and beyond....'a chain of informed conversations about peace building, truth and power'. also met the emergency poet..deborah alma, who amongst other publications edited #metoo a woman's poetry anthology and the emergency poet....an anti-stress poetry anthology. wonderful!  so much to explore and consider at a time when it sometimes feels that 'the world is imploding/exploding....what can we do to help restore balance? we can start with ourselves and for me there is always yoga which in simple terms  means unity of body, mind and spirit. yoga is so restorative and what is great about being a yoga teacher is that you can share it!  #worldconflictresolutionday #emergencypoet #worldpeaceflame  ##druyoga #dru #conflictresolution #peacestudies

text:
🕯tonya - @brckhmptn 🕯
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
this is not for anyone. this is for me. to get this off my chest and be done hoarding it. i’m not looking for anyones pity, sympathy or for anyone to even believe me.
.
.
.
🛑trigger warning: abuse, csa, depression🛑
.
as a kid, i was left alone a lot, i felt alone a lot. i kept to myself, never really got along with kids my age and adults didn’t want me hanging around them; constantly hearing “get lost.” mom worked long hours at demanding jobs my whole life. and while i know and am grateful that she did the best could to support five kids on her own; she was never emotionally available. while, i may not have been neglected on purpose, i was neglected nonetheless. i think that’s why i was so easily manipulated and agreed to keep secrets by those whom i was taught were meant to love and protect me.
for as long as i can remember (literally, i don’t know how young i was when it started) i was molested by my grandfather. it didn’t fully stop till i moved out of my mom’s house after high school. i don’t wanna go into the traumatic details; just that it’s really fucked up and it has left me extremely fucked up. it disrupts my life on a daily basis in all aspects of my life.
i dissociate so much and so often, i’m constantly being asked if “i’m okay” or if i’m just “spacing out”. i’m not okay, i start thinking about my past and my mind forces me to stop feeling it by disconnecting my emotions from my thoughts and i feel disconnected from myself and reality. i’m severely depressed and although, i’m not suicidal; most days i do wish i wasn’t born. i’m filled with anger; at myself for my silence, at him for ruining my childhood and my adolescence, at the relationships (friendship or romantic) that were destroyed or never got the chance to even start, at the world for being so ignorant and hateful. everything can feel so overwhelming, at times i feel like i’m gonna explode from all the pressure built up within me. and i don’t know how to let it go.
to me, the second photo of me is how i feel and look like on the inside. eyes cast downward with no real expression or emotion on my face.
i’m just trying to better myself for myself.

text:
sometimes i get lonely surrounded by people i love. it’s been a thing for me ever since i was a teenager going through depression. back then, my worst fear was being surrounded by people i loved yet still feeling all alone. like i could be screaming for the love and belonging i needed, yet no one’s love would be enough. that i would live in perpetual isolation. as the depression lifted that fear started to dissipate, but the feeling of being lonely has come true from time to time. i think it’s simply human or maybe my human experience at least.

this feeling finds me on days after being around a group of people and being super extroverted. it finds me when i don’t feel super connected to my husband when our work lives are crazy. it finds me after i talk to an old friend and wish we lived closer. it finds me when i’m at home with my children all day or when i haven’t seen my parents in awhile. 
it doesn’t freak me out as much as it once did. it’s familiar for me now. instead of wishing i never felt this way, i’ve come to embrace it when it moves in for a few hours or a day. i sit with it, observe it, and eventually it moves on. 
humaning comes with so many emotions. i’ve spent so much time analyzing them versus simply being their witness. i’m leaning into witnessing more, questioning less. maybe not everything needs to be understood or has a purpose. maybe little pieces of our hearts travel outside our bodies to be with other people or times in space from time to time. maybe that’s all loneliness is until we call these pieces back to ourselves. 
that’s my perspective today at least. so, i’ll be here, calling myself back home, back whole. and onward we’ll go my friends 💗

text_retweet:
#repost @stories.of.art (@get_repost)
・・・
“now that is girl power”, said my daughter when she saw this painting. the lady we see is timoclea, a noble woman from thebes. her city led a revolt agains alexander the great, which as it turned out, was not the smartest of plans. alexander came, conquered and sacked the place. one of alexanders captains found timoclea and raped her. then he asked her if she had any money hidden away. she said she hid it in her well. when he bent over to look, she pushed him in. then threw rocks at him until he was dead. so far, so good, but then she was caught. they brought her before alexander. there she explained clearly and with dignity all that had happened. the king was so impressed that he did not punish her for killing his man. instead he ordered his officers to make sure there would be no more abuse of women and children in the city. after i told her this, my daughter (10) commented that there are two roll models in this story. there is the lady who stood up for herself and punished her attacker, but there is also the man who took her seriously and did what he could to stop this from happening again. when i look at them, i know she and her sisters will become strong and confident women who will stand up for themselves no matter what. i am less sure we can get more people to take victims seriously. and i worry that until we do, we will need to dig a lot more wells. .
timoclea, elisabetta sirani, 1659, museo di capodimonte, naples. .

text: periods really aren’t an easy thing to deal with, they take over our lives for 3-8 days, sometimes more. due to my birth control, i bled for two weeks every month. don’t ever make light of it, you’ll never understand unless you go through it yourself. being on your period can also inflame anxiety and depression, making it so much worse. some girls get it so young, i was 11 years old. my grandmother was 10. periods are not something to make a joke out of.

text: october is domestic abuse awareness month. domestic violence is something no one should ever have to go through. being a victim, now a survivor my number one thing i want ppl to stop doing is asking why didn’t or why don’t you just leave. “just” leaving isn’t a simple option. if it was, ppl would “just” leave. leaving sometimes brings far worse outcomes. when i finally got the courage to leave not only did it affect my self but my friends, family, and co workers. they suffered endless days and nights of harassment. i was forced to leave my home, experienced a shelter, friendships cancelled, being a transy (floating between homes) my money was stolen, job was on the brinks. going through the court system was something on a whole other level unimaginable.  had to fight like crazy to keep my daughter because of the lies that were told just to spite me. lived in fear for over 3 years all because i left. during those years, i blamed myself for leaving. had i stayed none of that would of happened. had i stayed i could of also been dead. not so many women are as lucky as i and can not tell their story. domestic violence has to stop!

text:
i always wanted to be a strong woman. 
empowered. confident. where my truth would flow freely. i never imagined that i would actually become her.
yesterday i spoke with lisa foster @parillume about sexual violation for my podcast pleasure rising @pleasurerising , i shared one of my experiences with sexual violation. it was the first time i shared publicly of my experience.
the old me would have really hid and felt shame. what would my family think? how would this effect my credibility?
i give zero fucks now. 
i will let my truth out, i will empower women to boldly become who they could only dream of becoming. 
it takes a ton of clearing, releasing, dismantling, designing, redesigning and tweaking.
but the process of rebirth is always, always welcome,  for everyone.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
breaking: we join our #nc09 neighbors in demading that dan mccready stop his campaign commercial that display #women who just wait for stereotype phone gossip at their kitchen table. #staywoke #countryoverparty #womensmarch "it's one thing to be bombarded with attack ads all day; but, stereotypes like women being gossip girls is too far.

that's why we join good people who are just baffled why dan mccready & nancy pelosi's dccc continue to run these stereotypes in attacks on mark harris about his religious preachings on women.

it hypocrisy! do catholics or other religions that don't promote women leadership? how does dan, marines, or his church treat women or #lgbtq?

neighbors who were awoken & disliked president 45 are not going to vote for mark harris. period! many are unaffiliated white women & white women democrats. these #metoo women may vote for dan.

neighbors who were awoken & disliked hillary clinton are not going to vote for dan mccready. period! many are unaffiliated white men & white women republicans. these #himtoo women may vote for mark.

so why on earth would dan mccready unveil another silly commercial that portrays women as stereotyped gossip teenagers with so many women of color & young women undecided?

in this mad men style commercial, a white middle aged women rushes  to search her computer for the latest juicy gossip.  she says, "mark harris said what?" dan sees white middle aged women differently than the rest of us. our women don't gossip on the phone like teenagers, they work, they read, they are not shocked weeks before an election! and they actually go to sports bars!

does this past the laugh test?

can anyone imagine a man in this same commercial? saying, "oh, he said what? i'm rushing to my table now! this is shocking!" let me be clear. no one is confused about our 3 choices. mark harris is a trump republican, jeff scott is an independent libertarian, & dan mccready is going to fix congress, china, cure aids & solve world peace because he's a marine!"-cc

#medicareforall #saveroe #medicalcannabis #abolishice #no287g #needtoimpeach #livingwage #corporatewelfare #flipthe9thnc #familyoverparty #gunreformnow?"-cc

most well-known for her activism on behalf of senior citizens, maggie kuhn also fought for human rights, social and economic justice, global peace, integration, urban renewal, and an improved understanding of mental health issues.

text:
day 45: tarana burke [born september 12, 1973]
•
 african-american civil rights activist from the bronx, new york who founded the me too movement. in 2006, burke began using the phrase "me too" to raise awareness of the pervasiveness of sexual abuse and assault in society, and the phrase developed into a broader movement, following the 2017 use of #metoo as a hashtag following the harvey weinstein sexual abuse allegations. time named burke, among a group of other prominent activists dubbed "the silence breakers", as the time person of the year for 2017. burke attends public speaking events across the country and is currently senior director at girls for gender equity. (source: wikipedia)
•

text: this makes me want to cry. it's hard for me to admit that but it does it makes my story in a way sound insignificant but it was terrifying for me so i'm gonna share it right here. i was 12 hanging out with a bunch of my 15yr old brothers friends at a playground there weren't many girls just one sitting beside me on a swing i acted much older then i was in a good way i wasn't childish like most 12yr olds i picked at the boys in a flirtatious way. a new boy walked up giving a greeting to the others like they knew each other let's call him danny, danny was 14 a nice looking boy with a smirk always on his face i figured well this should be fun his attention came to me and my friend on the swings she was 14 as well but he was paying attention to me mostly. he knew the kind of game i played and he played quite good. so here i am swinging and he smacks my ass i'm in shock i dont say much he does it again i tell him to stop it catches the attention of a friend of mine a 16yr old much bigger then danny. let's call him chase, chase is a sweetheart he chases danny down several times telling him to back off but danny doesn't listen. chase has danny and i finally hop off the swing and walk over and smack him in the face. he walks off all sad like and i almost feel bad yet relieved. fast forward a month we are at a new location and our friends are talking about their friend who is coming tomorrow danny by this time o had forgotten all about him so i'm like cool. then i see him i stand still but i'm blowing up inside like this jerk really he is nice for a day or so and i'm like ok maybe he's ok then he starts to act jerky again saying volgar things doing things behind my back literally! but then he becomes kinda like a friend like i don't know what is wrong with me i am trusting this guy again. we went on a walk (his idea) then we get to this path that leads off into the woods i have been down there before it leads to a fishing spot and a few other secluded spot. he's like wanna come see this cool spot i say no i need to head back (i actually did need to) the horrible thing is at the time i was not even thinking that if i had went it could have been dangerous. #metoo

text:
click link in bio to read the entire post☝🏻☝🏻☝🏻☝🏻☝🏻 lately, i’ve been hard on myself for not being as active on social media as i ought to be. i struggle with anxiety, ptsd, and depression. it truly is a battle every single day. i have “so much” potential and have “so many” marvelous ideas; and what is stopping me....that rush of anxiety that builds up in my chest, it gets so tight i can’t breathe; i can’t see straight; i become paralyzed. 
i am not writing this to have anyone tell me they are sorry, i don’t want pity. i want those who are struggling to realize you’re not alone. i want those who don’t understand those who suffer with mental ailments to continue to be empathetic and open-minded. i want to share my struggles in hopes that if just one person who reads this realizes they are not alone. and your not! or if one person is close to someone struggling their own battle, know you are not alone either. you are an angel. 
even if you aren’t told by the one suffering thank you, or how much you are appreciated; know that you are a god sent. some who struggle have a hard time opening up due to the stigma that goes along with mental illness.
.
.
.
#mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #anxiety #ptsd #depression #metoo #yournotalone #mentalillness #struggleisreal #keepfighting #surroundyourselfwithpositivepeople #surroundyourselfwithgoodpeople #youareloved #takecareofyou #youcomefirst #breannmcgregor

text:
hace tiempo he querido retratar a nicole, hoy les acompaño esta ilustración con una reflexión con la cual me identifico. no tenemos siempre que estar de acuerdo con las personas que amamos. "no odio a mi mamá en absoluto, sólo que ella también puede estar equivocada. 
desde hace mucho tiempo, he considerado que es innecesario el discutir por tonterías, pero a lo largo de mi crecimiento me he dado cuenta de que si no lo hago, la gente no dejará de pensar como lo hace, no les dará vergüenza decir lo que dicen.
mi papá siempre me ha dicho que a las personas mayores se les debe respeto, pero claro está, que debe ser mutuo. mi mamá es una persona machista, y me molesta, tiende a decir comentarios como "si sales con shorts cortos (sic), no te quejes cuando te agarren una nalga", pero también es insensata con sus hijos, como cuando mi hermanito tomó demasiado y puso a una chama a besarlo. el punto es que he creado una aflicción tal sobre la mujer, una mujer que me parece incomprensible, porque me parezco tanto a ella, pero al mismo tiempo soy todo lo contrario, a veces puede ser la más comprensiva y me hace amarla, pero luego dice comentarios asquerosos y se molesta conmigo por reclamarle. 
no sé si esto mejorará o si verá esto y se enojará más, pero sólo quiero que tengan en cuenta una reflexión: no le deben nada a nadie, no están obligados a cambiar sus creencias si de verdad no lo creen necesario. por mucho que ames a una persona, esa persona también puede equivocarse" .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
pia camil’s “bara bara bara” approximates the makeshift tented markets of latin american urban landscapes and occupied the heart of fair market. in an entirely new configuration from its previous iterations. the work is created by sewing together hundreds of used t-shirts that have made their ways back and forth across the us/ mexico border—arriving for sale in las torres market in iztapalapa, a neighborhood of mexico city, to be bought and integrated into this artwork which has now traveled over much of the united states. the apparel utilized in this work reminds of the way that text-based messaging and slogans transmit ideas across borders to become absorbed within cultural manifestations.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non-traditional venue.

fair. was generously supported by swire properties inc, in partnership with the john s. and james l. knight foundation. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

fair. was generously suppoed by swire propeies inc, in panership with the john s. and james l. knight foundation. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
virginity testing is directly linked to crimes of their so called honor ! ending #virginitytesting will lead to ending #crimesofhonor and reduce #violenceagainatwomen ! 
لازم نفهموا مليح مصادر العنف ضد المرأة و التمييز الموجود ضدها لكي نقضي على مثل هاته الظاهرة من المصدر. جسدي ملكية خصوصية و أنا وحدي من لدي حق التصرف فيه و معرفة حميمياته، علاقاتي الجنسية ليس قضية عائلية أو مجتمعاتية! أضف إلى ذلك، قد أثبتت دراسات علمية حديثة أنه لا توجد هناك أي وسيلة أثبتت نجاحتها بنسبة 100٪ فيما يخص القدرة على التحقق من سلامة غشاء البكارة! هناك من لا غشاء لها و علميا غشاء البكارة يبدأ في التلاشي تدريجيا مباشرة بعد سن البلوغ أي بعد إنتفاء الغرض من وجوده! (وظيفة غشاء البكارة هو إغلاق فتحة المهبل عند الفتاة الصغيرة لحماية الأعضاء الداخلية من الجراثيم و الإلتهابات، في حين الإفرازات المهبلية الحمضية التي تبدأ في الظهور مع سن البلوغ vaginal discharge تقوم بهذه الوظيفة و تقتل جميع الجراثيم و المكروبات المحيطة مما يلغي الحاجة لوجود غشاء للحماية فيبدأ هذا الأخير بالإضمحلال و التلاشي) شيء آخر، العذرية سيداتي أوانسي سادتي هي : كل إنسان لم يحقق ذروة جنسية ناتجة عن إتصاله مع إنسان آخر يسمى بتول أو عذراء، ولا علاقة لمفهوم العذرية بغشاء البكارة! انهوا إختبارات العذرية في #الجزائر !!!! #إختبارات_العذرية #العذرية #ثقافة_جنسية #جسد_المرأة #العالم_العربي #العالم_الإسلامي #جرائم_الشرف #لا_شرف_في_جرائم_الشرف #لن_أحمي_المتحرشين_بعد_اليوم #لا_للتحرش_اللفظي #في_بلادك_تقدري #لا_لإختبارات_العذرية_في_الجزائر

text:
📖
in her innocence, she never bothered about other people's sexuality.
after years of working with gay co-workers she realized their boss had no idea that of all 10 employees including bosses, only 4 were straight.
she didn't know she had a very pointless "gaydar".
whenever she entered a club, without fail, gay women would approach her only to be confused by the answer "i'm not gay.".
there were never any issues regarding her own sexuality - not even when she fell in love with a girl.
in fact, after pondering about it, her answer would still be: "i like men."
maybe she liked to dress "boyishly" or maybe she had found an effective way to protect herself in a world of abusers.
the naivety of her existence would pour out of her, inexplicably and involuntarily.
putting her in situations where only poetry could be the answer.
#writersofinstagram #loveislove #metoo #thefutureisfemale #shortstories #thisisasafezone

text:
a year ago today i was writing in my journal, complaining, if i'm being honest, about feeling aimless and adrift. i took a break from the whine-fest to scroll facebook for a bit, and came across a couple of posts from women who were struggling to be on social media dur to trauma triggers, and though they didn't say it specifically, i assumed it was because of the #metoo movement. i thought, "lord, these women don't have a single person they can talk to about what they're struggling with," and do you know what i realized for the first time?
.
they can talk to me.
. 
a million ideas came together in that moment, and right then my first sexual abuse recovery group was born. now a year has passed and we've grown from a group of 6 with one leader to a group of nearly 30 with a whole team of leaders. we have a name, hope for her, and a vision to see hope for her groups in churches all over our community and beyond. what began with prayer and a weekly journal entry has become a complete workbook with leaders' guide that's almost ready to publish. all that's left is raising the funds to pay for it all - something i've never embarked on before but i'm looking forward to seeing how god provides. suffice it to say, when i was complaining in my journal that day, i never dreamed this is where i was going. i've shared before that i probably wouldn't have chosen it, but i wouldn't change it for anything else in th world.

our time has come to fully rise and step into our power and back into our remembering of who we are.

the more we see ourselves in our divine light the more undeniable it will be to be seen as anything but truth. 
love to you sister, i stand by you in this fight and i will not rest until we have equal victory. 🔥🏹🐺

text:
⬇️⬇️⬇️read the caption⬇️⬇️⬇️ @regran_ed from @veganasfuck7 -  #bethechange
#soallmaylive
a former dairy cow was so saddened by memories of her previous babies being taken away by a farmer that she hid her newborn calf to keep her from being taken, too.

clarabelle was rescued from a dairy farm in late november by the australian farm sanctuary edgar's mission. she was hours away from slaughter at the farm, where her milk production was too low to bother keeping her #alive. when clarabelle arrived at the rescue, volunteers discovered she was #pregnant.

a week before her due date, volunteers noticed that clarabelle was acting strange - normally eager to eat, she was staying at a distance and acting wary. after a bit of a search, they discovered that she had secretly given birth and hidden the baby in a nearby patch of tall grass.

cows are known for their deep #maternal instincts. dr. holly cheever documented a story from her early days as a dairy veterinarian where a pregnant cow, knowing that her farmer would take away her baby, gave birth to twins and took only one back to the farmer.

she kept the other hidden away in the pasture until the farmer noticed her reduced milk production, found the baby, and took it away too.

pam ahern, the founder of edgar's mission, recounted the story of another rescue cow named pixie. "pixie herself was very young, way too young to have been mated," ahern told the dodo. "but pixie was very, very protective and loving of her baby. although a first-time mother, and a very young one at that, the maternal instinct was very strong and one we determined never to break." luckily this baby - named valentine, as she was born on feb. 14 - is also destined for a better life than most dairy cows and will remain at the sanctuary with her mother.
_

text:
at 11:00 am today, beit ruth staff and girls gathered to participate in a nationwide demonstration to highlight the issue of violence against women in israel, where 20 women have been murdered due to domestic violence in 2018. 
for our girls, this was an important event to attend, as a majority of them have witnessed violence in the past. 
as an effort to break the cycle of violence and to protect the girls from violence in the future, we discussed the warning signals of an abusive partner and the existing emergency channels.

at beit ruth, we help girls heal from their trauma and overcome their past experiences. with your support, we give these girls a second chance in life. 
today, we take a moment to remember the many victims of domestic violence, and we say out loud: never again.

#neveragain #vaw #womenempowerment #domesticviolence #girlpower #metoo #israel

text:
[ tonight / ce soir ]

take back the night is a public event organized by the south east sexual assault centre @sesac.casse that demands action against gender-based violence that forces women and children to live in fear. this annual international event is a great opportunity to rediscover our voice and our right to safety. 📢
.
using an inclusive definition of “woman” and “female”, the space welcome trans women, genderqueer women, and non-binary people. men are also inviting to the event, we ask that they be present as support to the walkers side.
.
reprenons la nuit est une manifestation publique organisée par le centre d'agression sexuelle sud-est @sesac.casse qui exige une action contre la violence sexiste qui oblige les femmes et les enfants à vivre dans la peur. cet événement international annuel est une formidable opportunité de retrouver notre voix et notre droit à la sécurité. 📢 .
l'espace utilise une définition inclusive de « femme » et souhaite la bienvenue aux femmes trans, aux femmes genderqueer et aux personnes non-binaires. les hommes sont aussi invités à l’événement, nous demandons qu’ils soient présents en tant que soutien au côté des marcheuses. .
.
.
.
.
#takebackthenight #reprenonslanuit #metoo #moiaussi #timesup #lgbtqia #antiviolence #womyn #femmes

text: yes that’s right, life really is this simple as long as i am sober, clean and realize that love is my focus today.  when i get into my mind too much,  i find myself in trouble.  i have found if i just get to a meeting, reach out to help someone else, smile at a child or spend time with a pet life comes back into focus. this allows me to clear my mind and see a clear reflection of what pure love is. yes it’s true that my mind is the only thing that causes suffering. once i learned to live from my heart i was able to find joy, happiness and peace no matter what is going on around me. #metooneveryou #sobrietyismylove #metoo #timesup #soberwomen #onedayatatime #aa #sobrietyquotes #traumahealing #sobrietyrocks #sobrietyquotes #recoveryispossible #billw #realrecovery #theshamelesswarrior #believeher
